WEBVTT

00:00:00.142 --> 00:00:01.578
Hey, it's Guillaume!

00:00:15.343 --> 00:00:15.830
How's it going?

00:00:17.442 --> 00:00:18.615
You guys aren't too tired, are you?

00:00:21.260 --> 00:00:25.579
Honestly, it can't be worse than me—I just got in from Miami and jet lag is hitting me hard.

00:00:27.320 --> 00:00:29.036
Anyone here use Whoop?

00:00:30.801 --> 00:00:33.034
If you use it, do you know what 1% in the red means?

00:00:34.939 --> 00:00:35.880
Alright, that's where I'm at.

00:00:37.161 --> 00:00:42.118
But hey, we're here, we have to deliver, and I'm really, really happy to see so many of you here,

00:00:44.079 --> 00:00:48.759
for these next two days, which usually happen on weekends, but today is Monday.

00:00:49.960 --> 00:00:52.140
So congrats to all of you for being here and making the time,

00:00:52.881 --> 00:00:58.880
I think I need to jump right into the talk, or they're going to ring the alarm on me,

00:00:59.100 --> 00:01:01.859
because they know I can go off on tangents sometimes.

00:01:03.962 --> 00:01:06.900
So, discipline and consistency are what get results.

00:01:07.843 --> 00:01:08.248
Let's go!

00:01:12.719 --> 00:01:17.900
So, what I thought would be really useful for you, since a lot of you are just starting out,

00:01:18.099 --> 00:01:21.599
is to share a few stories—I picked out 8 of them—

00:01:22.742 --> 00:01:25.579
that took me from zero to where I am today.

00:01:26.061 --> 00:01:31.680
We'll dig into the details, because it's important to get back to basics, especially when you're starting out,

00:01:31.939 --> 00:01:36.659
and sometimes it's tough to take that first step, so I want to show you how things can unfold,

00:01:37.240 --> 00:01:40.311
with some mindset shifts you need to make.

00:01:40.331 --> 00:01:42.980
So, mindset shifts—basically, changes in how you think,

00:01:43.159 --> 00:01:47.180
in your philosophy—that's really my goal, to help you unlock your next step.

00:01:47.739 --> 00:01:48.825
Alright?

00:01:48.844 --> 00:01:52.200
We're also going to look at 10 rules I borrowed from one of my mentors, Jim Rohn,

00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:55.033
which are great reminders for your own success.

00:01:55.054 --> 00:01:56.179
Why don't people take action?

00:01:56.420 --> 00:01:58.570
I think that's an interesting observation.

00:01:58.611 --> 00:02:00.099
Who here today isn't taking action?

00:02:01.141 --> 00:02:02.579
Ah, I expected no one would raise their hand.

00:02:05.599 --> 00:02:07.614
Honestly, who finds it hard to take action?

00:02:09.480 --> 00:02:11.768
Can we give ourselves a round of applause, please?

00:02:11.828 --> 00:02:15.780
And can the people who do take action clap too?

00:02:15.881 --> 00:02:17.740
There you go, that's important because...

00:02:20.401 --> 00:02:22.915
We're here to cheer you on.

00:02:22.936 --> 00:02:23.258
Alright?

00:02:23.741 --> 00:02:25.560
So one of the main goals is really going to be that.

00:02:25.741 --> 00:02:27.034
The idea is to have some breakthroughs.

00:02:27.055 --> 00:02:27.296
Okay?

00:02:27.661 --> 00:02:29.740
In this talk, some things will seem obvious to you,

00:02:29.759 --> 00:02:34.080
and some things you'll think, "Ah, that's exactly what I needed to hear,

00:02:34.221 --> 00:02:35.010
and especially to put into practice."

00:02:35.740 --> 00:02:38.879
By the way, if you have a notebook or somewhere to write, or can take notes,

00:02:39.301 --> 00:02:41.939
I'd like you to take notes in two ways.

00:02:42.941 --> 00:02:45.800
You'll take regular notes, but it's really important to have one more thing,

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:47.655
a separate sheet called "Action."

00:02:48.361 --> 00:02:49.998
And on the action sheet, every time you hear something,

00:02:50.159 --> 00:02:51.759
and you think, "Okay, I need to start doing that,"

00:02:51.780 --> 00:02:53.860
you'll put a 1 in front, and write down the action.

00:02:54.461 --> 00:02:55.044
2, 3, 4.

00:02:55.063 --> 00:02:58.340
So by the end of these 48 hours, you'll have an action plan.

00:02:58.722 --> 00:03:01.400
about exactly what you've learned, so you can actually put it into practice,

00:03:01.599 --> 00:03:03.159
because a lot of people take notes and never look at them again.

00:03:03.721 --> 00:03:05.098
Some of you probably recognize yourselves in that.

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:09.300
So the goal is to take action on this, plus I'll give you 7 extra tips.

00:03:09.621 --> 00:03:09.703
Alright?

00:03:10.540 --> 00:03:12.556
Who's already been to one of my talks?

00:03:13.800 --> 00:03:15.439
Okay, yeah, that's true, we don't have the same style.

00:03:17.102 --> 00:03:18.377
Alright, let's clap, let's try clapping.

00:03:18.762 --> 00:03:20.056
Who's already seen one of my conferences?

00:03:20.942 --> 00:03:22.014
Okay, who’s never seen me before?

00:03:23.343 --> 00:03:23.889
Alright, about half and half.

00:03:24.335 --> 00:03:24.657
Cool, nice.

00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:30.719
So, my goal is to explain how I went from zero

00:03:31.822 --> 00:03:35.780
to over 100 million dollars in profits with my partners,

00:03:36.441 --> 00:03:40.938
with no network at the start, because usually, we all start out alone,

00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:43.639
unless there are some twins in the room, maybe.

00:03:45.383 --> 00:03:46.680
No money at the beginning, no experience.

00:03:48.060 --> 00:03:51.340
I started out as an electrician on construction sites,

00:03:53.042 --> 00:03:55.139
my dad put me on job sites when I was 15,

00:03:56.061 --> 00:03:58.734
for the summer, so I could see what real work was like.

00:04:00.901 --> 00:04:02.500
Then I washed glasses in nightclubs.

00:04:03.901 --> 00:04:06.319
I was a glass washer, that's what they called it—super glamorous.

00:04:07.722 --> 00:04:10.318
Alongside my studies, just to make, I remember, 60 euros.

00:04:12.102 --> 00:04:14.800
It was cool, it was good, it let me earn a bit more money.

00:04:15.102 --> 00:04:16.560
Then I worked in a private bank,

00:04:17.401 --> 00:04:20.699
where I was chasing down lost checks, that kind of thing.

00:04:21.579 --> 00:04:22.839
Yeah, crazy, but I did it.

00:04:23.982 --> 00:04:24.889
On a fixed-term contract, making 1700 euros a month.

00:04:27.122 --> 00:04:28.978
Then I moved to Geneva.

00:04:29.925 --> 00:04:30.978
I worked for a company,

00:04:31.199 --> 00:04:34.720
I did business development for a company selling translation services.

00:04:35.845 --> 00:04:36.779
So yeah, I was in business development.

00:04:37.182 --> 00:04:38.119
At the same time, we started investing.

00:04:38.601 --> 00:04:40.480
Then I joined JP Morgan in private banking,

00:04:40.600 --> 00:04:41.500
I got the chance to do that.

00:04:42.786 --> 00:04:43.579
But I really didn't like it at all.

00:04:43.843 --> 00:04:44.939
On the second day, I wanted to quit.

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:47.738
So I wanted to stop—well, I actually quit after 7 months.

00:04:48.584 --> 00:04:49.598
I still managed to stick it out for 7 months.

00:04:50.139 --> 00:04:50.608
I trained myself.

00:04:51.882 --> 00:04:54.019
We're going to talk a lot about training and taking action too.

00:04:54.699 --> 00:04:57.779
And then I was lucky enough to get into real estate, you'll see,

00:04:59.083 --> 00:05:00.360
for my very first deals.

00:05:00.540 --> 00:05:01.839
And that's where I am today.

00:05:01.839 --> 00:05:05.339
So really, just to say, to echo what Mathieu said,

00:05:05.762 --> 00:05:06.939
this really is for everyone.

00:05:07.380 --> 00:05:12.540
It doesn't matter where you come from, or what you studied, whatever.

00:05:12.800 --> 00:05:14.319
Because today, people have all kinds of backgrounds.

00:05:14.519 --> 00:05:16.680
You all have your own story, and you can all write it,

00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:17.279
it's up to you to do it.

00:05:18.519 --> 00:05:20.839
So today, just to give you some numbers,

00:05:21.101 --> 00:05:22.678
over 327 million dollars invested,

00:05:23.101 --> 00:05:25.579
more than 45 deals, tens of millions in profits made,

00:05:25.720 --> 00:05:26.115
I've already mentioned that.

00:05:26.980 --> 00:05:30.600
So the problem is, according to the stats,

00:05:30.822 --> 00:05:32.415
in the room, it was about like this,

00:05:32.939 --> 00:05:37.540
70% beginners, 30% people who've done at least one deal, maybe more.

00:05:38.142 --> 00:05:39.240
But you all have the same hang-ups.

00:05:39.882 --> 00:05:40.815
So what are those blocks?

00:05:45.040 --> 00:05:47.016
Who here has trouble with financing today?

00:05:47.682 --> 00:05:48.035
Okay.

00:05:49.103 --> 00:05:50.079
Right, I need to pick.

00:05:51.581 --> 00:05:53.016
Who has a problem with financing?

00:05:53.899 --> 00:05:53.964
Okay.

00:05:54.841 --> 00:05:55.879
Actually, why do I want you to raise your hand?

00:05:56.060 --> 00:05:58.819
It's because I want you to take advantage of the people around you,

00:05:58.819 --> 00:06:00.480
so you can spot who else is struggling with that.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:02.360
Because maybe they could be a solution for you.

00:06:02.699 --> 00:06:04.779
So if you don't mind, let's do this hand-raising style.

00:06:05.160 --> 00:06:05.259
Okay.

00:06:05.901 --> 00:06:07.173
So who has a problem with financing?

00:06:08.141 --> 00:06:08.314
Okay.

00:06:09.420 --> 00:06:11.112
Who has trouble finding partners?

00:06:12.521 --> 00:06:12.651
Okay.

00:06:14.021 --> 00:06:15.598
Who struggles with time management?

00:06:16.982 --> 00:06:18.439
No, I want to see every hand up, please.

00:06:20.040 --> 00:06:22.519
This is a challenge we all face.

00:06:22.939 --> 00:06:23.233
Alright.

00:06:25.004 --> 00:06:26.259
I put time management under structuring.

00:06:26.480 --> 00:06:26.600
Okay.

00:06:26.779 --> 00:06:27.978
Who here struggles with scaling?

00:06:28.202 --> 00:06:28.795
How do you speed things up?

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:30.737
How do you go faster?

00:06:31.230 --> 00:06:31.357
Okay.

00:06:32.903 --> 00:06:34.278
So, that's kind of the goal here.

00:06:35.242 --> 00:06:38.439
The goal of my talk, and of the other speakers you'll hear,

00:06:38.519 --> 00:06:43.379
is really to help you set up a space, an environment to find your business partners.

00:06:43.379 --> 00:06:45.680
I met Yann at an event.

00:06:47.002 --> 00:06:49.079
I was all the way at the back of the room.

00:06:49.624 --> 00:06:50.540
He was the speaker.

00:06:51.581 --> 00:06:54.699
And at the end, I waited until, I think, it was 4 in the morning.

00:06:55.564 --> 00:06:56.480
Back then, I used to drink alcohol.

00:06:57.946 --> 00:06:58.478
We were having a good time.

00:07:00.519 --> 00:07:05.279
And I just thought, there's no way I'm leaving

00:07:05.824 --> 00:07:07.500
without going up to him and showing him what I do.

00:07:07.839 --> 00:07:08.660
I told him, 'What do I do?'

00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:09.113
I shared my vision.

00:07:10.021 --> 00:07:10.699
We're going to talk about vision.

00:07:10.860 --> 00:07:11.339
It's important.

00:07:11.839 --> 00:07:14.100
We're also going to talk about negotiations all afternoon.

00:07:15.122 --> 00:07:15.838
Know how to sell yourself.

00:07:16.899 --> 00:07:17.055
Sell.

00:07:17.500 --> 00:07:20.180
Inspire people, give them a vision so they want to join you.

00:07:21.225 --> 00:07:22.420
It's at events like this.

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:24.339
That's how I met Yann.

00:07:24.721 --> 00:07:29.918
Who here would have liked to team up with Yann Darwin to boost their business deals?

00:07:30.540 --> 00:07:30.603
Okay.

00:07:32.062 --> 00:07:34.360
Just remember, today, your Yann Darwin is in this room.

00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.800
And honestly, that's pretty likely.

00:07:38.841 --> 00:07:41.220
So, in this room, there are people making a lot of money.

00:07:42.541 --> 00:07:43.740
There are people making a lot of money.

00:07:44.360 --> 00:07:48.658
There are people who, even at their level, are telling me they really want to 10x their results.

00:07:49.702 --> 00:07:50.779
You have to go find those people.

00:07:51.839 --> 00:07:53.319
And there are people who aren't really sure where they're at.

00:07:54.302 --> 00:07:55.920
We're here to help guide you a bit.

00:07:57.779 --> 00:07:59.399
So that's really the goal.

00:07:59.802 --> 00:08:02.199
Beyond the content, beyond the training, it's really about networking.

00:08:02.964 --> 00:08:03.699
And that's what makes the difference.

00:08:03.819 --> 00:08:09.980
That's why I'll always encourage you to show up every year at every event you can,

00:08:10.401 --> 00:08:12.939
as long as you're with the right people, in the right places,

00:08:13.540 --> 00:08:17.160
and you know you're surrounded by people who want the best for you too.

00:08:17.360 --> 00:08:19.019
Because we're here to help all of you make money.

00:08:19.444 --> 00:08:20.819
That's my goal, our goal, everyone's goal here.

00:08:22.661 --> 00:08:25.500
So, find partners, move faster, raise funds, and learn.

00:08:25.740 --> 00:08:25.809
Okay.

00:08:26.642 --> 00:08:27.699
I think we're done with the intro.

00:08:29.021 --> 00:08:29.435
We're good.

00:08:30.461 --> 00:08:35.539
So, what you're going to learn is how to go from zero to your first deal,

00:08:36.302 --> 00:08:37.899
for those of you who are just starting out,

00:08:39.100 --> 00:08:42.758
or if you've done one deal and you're thinking, 'I'm stuck, the banks, all that stuff.'

00:08:43.299 --> 00:08:46.080
I'm going to try to unlock all those situations so you can do more deals.

00:08:46.542 --> 00:08:47.759
You'll also learn a bit about structuring.

00:08:48.423 --> 00:08:49.456
How do you structure a deal?

00:08:49.961 --> 00:08:52.960
How do you make an offer that actually makes sense for a partner to join you,

00:08:53.402 --> 00:08:54.355
or for one of your investors?

00:08:55.043 --> 00:08:55.990
How do you scale up, basically?

00:08:57.201 --> 00:08:58.700
So, definition of a marchand de biens.

00:08:59.240 --> 00:09:00.698
What is a marchand de biens?

00:09:01.919 --> 00:09:07.240
Well, a marchand de biens needs to have a pretty wide range of skills.

00:09:08.140 --> 00:09:11.360
First, you have to be a chasseur, a hunter.

00:09:11.659 --> 00:09:13.899
You'll see, but sometimes English words just pop into my head.

00:09:14.761 --> 00:09:15.405
Okay?

00:09:15.426 --> 00:09:17.480
It's not to show off, it's just how it is.

00:09:18.100 --> 00:09:18.865
Okay?

00:09:18.885 --> 00:09:20.820
If you don't know me yet, you'll get used to it.

00:09:21.881 --> 00:09:23.479
So, a hunter is a chasseur.

00:09:25.484 --> 00:09:26.919
So that's someone who goes out and hunts for properties.

00:09:29.163 --> 00:09:30.860
Second, you need to be a dealmaker.

00:09:31.860 --> 00:09:33.057
What's a dealmaker?

00:09:33.581 --> 00:09:38.700
It's someone who can actually put together and structure a deal, bringing all the parties to the table.

00:09:39.760 --> 00:09:44.279
Sellers, buyers, investors, bankers—all the different parties involved.

00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:46.078
So, you need some real skills for this.

00:09:47.701 --> 00:09:53.080
Because, do you really think a real estate agent has the same profile as a banker?

00:09:54.302 --> 00:09:54.980
Uh, not really, no.

00:09:56.163 --> 00:09:57.116
Maybe sometimes, but not really.

00:09:57.620 --> 00:10:01.379
You’ll have to deal with different skill sets, different personalities.

00:10:02.424 --> 00:10:03.220
And you need to understand them.

00:10:03.360 --> 00:10:05.759
We’ll get into that a lot more this afternoon, especially the negotiation part.

00:10:05.799 --> 00:10:07.460
You’re a negotiator, you’re a salesperson too.

00:10:09.481 --> 00:10:11.919
You’re an operator, someone who understands renovation work,

00:10:12.642 --> 00:10:14.379
or who partners with someone who manages the work.

00:10:15.008 --> 00:10:15.480
We’ll talk more about that.

00:10:15.821 --> 00:10:18.320
But above all, you’re someone who creates value.

00:10:19.280 --> 00:10:23.679
If you want to raise money, your number one goal is to ask yourself,

00:10:23.902 --> 00:10:25.434
“How am I going to create value?”

00:10:26.163 --> 00:10:26.580
With your property.

00:10:27.061 --> 00:10:29.159
And you need to know how to structure deals.

00:10:30.104 --> 00:10:31.155
Uh, wow!

00:10:31.721 --> 00:10:34.758
So, you’ll see today, we’re going to have some laughs,

00:10:35.484 --> 00:10:36.759
we’re going to have fun, but we might cry too.

00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:37.547
Alright?

00:10:38.283 --> 00:10:40.120
Honestly, it makes me want to cry when I see my face like this,

00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:41.340
but it’s all good.

00:10:41.542 --> 00:10:42.698
We’re here to take you behind the scenes.

00:10:43.041 --> 00:10:43.245
Okay?

00:10:43.900 --> 00:10:45.458
So let's jump right in with the first story

00:10:45.761 --> 00:10:47.176
which goes back to December 2, 2011.

00:10:48.344 --> 00:10:49.240
Man, that doesn't make me feel any younger.

00:10:50.065 --> 00:10:50.960
Back then, I wore glasses.

00:10:51.679 --> 00:10:54.100
Best investment of my life: I got eye surgery.

00:10:54.240 --> 00:10:54.756
That worked out great, by the way.

00:10:55.960 --> 00:10:56.840
But anyway, that's another topic.

00:10:57.799 --> 00:10:59.339
I'll share little tips like that with you too.

00:11:00.881 --> 00:11:03.080
So here I am in Le Canet, eating super healthy,

00:11:03.240 --> 00:11:04.778
a nice pizza, right in the middle of moving.

00:11:06.302 --> 00:11:09.000
And actually, what you don't see here is that,

00:11:09.280 --> 00:11:11.000
I'm starting to make money, I'm in Switzerland,

00:11:11.681 --> 00:11:14.639
and everyone keeps telling me, you know, once you start making a bit of money,

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:17.616
a bit of money—back then I was at 60,000 Swiss francs a year, anyway,

00:11:18.179 --> 00:11:21.360
whatever, that was about 50,000 euros, maybe a bit less.

00:11:22.623 --> 00:11:23.840
So I'm thinking, what should I do?

00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:24.960
I'm starting to have a bit of money and all that.

00:11:25.019 --> 00:11:26.620
Everyone tells me, you have to invest in real estate,

00:11:26.861 --> 00:11:27.659
invest in real estate, and so on.

00:11:28.200 --> 00:11:29.073
So what do I do?

00:11:29.725 --> 00:11:30.399
I invest in real estate.

00:11:30.980 --> 00:11:31.725
So what do I do next?

00:11:31.745 --> 00:11:34.740
Since I had zero experience, zero training,

00:11:35.604 --> 00:11:36.500
but I was starting to have some money.

00:11:37.379 --> 00:11:41.259
By the way, I was working in Geneva, Switzerland, so I was living pretty well,

00:11:41.440 --> 00:11:43.919
You see, I’m making just over 3,000 now, whereas sometimes, well,

00:11:44.421 --> 00:11:45.980
when you’re starting out in France, it was a bit trickier,

00:11:46.100 --> 00:11:50.000
so I feel like, you know, I’ve got 3,000 euros a month, I’m loaded.

00:11:51.822 --> 00:11:53.360
I started buying and investing in real estate.

00:11:53.639 --> 00:11:54.471
I’m the boss!

00:11:56.404 --> 00:11:56.958
Yeah, yeah, the boss.

00:11:58.043 --> 00:11:59.320
So, I did everything you’re not supposed to do.

00:12:00.960 --> 00:12:03.139
I bought in Canet, because I’m originally from Nice,

00:12:04.081 --> 00:12:06.259
but I live in Geneva, I work in Geneva.

00:12:07.383 --> 00:12:08.740
Well, I couldn’t buy in Switzerland.

00:12:09.679 --> 00:12:12.159
I tried to buy in Switzerland, but it’s tough to get started here.

00:12:13.143 --> 00:12:14.759
So I said, okay, I’ll go down south.

00:12:15.600 --> 00:12:19.799
So I find an apartment, great, I meet the real estate agent in Nice.

00:12:20.322 --> 00:12:21.500
He offers me a deal in Canet.

00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:24.019
Okay, so you can already see the little problem.

00:12:25.240 --> 00:12:27.659
Then I check it out, it’s still a good buy, the price is alright.

00:12:27.759 --> 00:12:30.940
I still do my homework, I look into it, because, you know, you’ve got to check a little.

00:12:31.701 --> 00:12:33.659
But actually, I don’t really take care of it, because I’m not there.

00:12:34.279 --> 00:12:34.856
I’m in Geneva.

00:12:36.041 --> 00:12:37.840
