00:15:45.005 --> 00:15:45.438
Stop right there.

00:15:46.301 --> 00:15:46.384
OK.

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:54.440
So, my point is, this is where I started learning, training, and understanding.

00:15:54.961 --> 00:16:01.220
And what was really interesting is that in the book I made,

00:16:01.259 --> 00:16:06.379
they had me write down all the mistakes I made and the lessons I learned.

00:16:07.600 --> 00:16:11.677
So, my first lesson—actually, I'm going to share them with you.

00:16:12.340 --> 00:16:16.340
So, they had me write down three financial mistakes you made.

00:16:16.601 --> 00:16:17.999
What lessons can you take from those mistakes?

00:16:18.221 --> 00:16:19.559
Take a few moments to jot down your thoughts.

00:16:20.022 --> 00:16:23.279
I encourage everyone to take a photo of this and do it yourself.

00:16:24.360 --> 00:16:26.639
It'll help you avoid making mistakes.

00:16:27.224 --> 00:16:27.638
First mistake.

00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:29.039
I never should've bought the Canet apartment.

00:16:29.922 --> 00:16:30.229
OK.

00:16:30.249 --> 00:16:30.535
Why?

00:16:30.942 --> 00:16:31.167
Boom!

00:16:31.187 --> 00:16:31.960
I start listing everything.

00:16:32.059 --> 00:16:32.620
So, let's go through them quickly.

00:16:33.942 --> 00:16:36.159
Don't rush into investment decisions.

00:16:37.371 --> 00:16:37.500
OK.

00:16:38.380 --> 00:16:41.340
Don't just look at a few properties and pick one.

00:16:41.841 --> 00:16:43.620
You want to check out 100 to find that one great deal.

00:16:44.201 --> 00:16:45.240
Well, that's the theory anyway.

00:16:45.600 --> 00:16:49.179
But honestly, you do need to visit a lot to get a feel for it.

00:16:49.361 --> 00:16:50.659
Me, I pretty much bought the first one I saw.

00:16:51.120 --> 00:16:51.899
I think it was just a great opportunity.

00:16:52.020 --> 00:16:52.993
You know, we saw two or three, right?

00:16:53.902 --> 00:16:56.138
Who else saw just two or three properties and jumped in like I did?

00:16:56.607 --> 00:16:56.754
No one?

00:16:56.940 --> 00:16:57.732
Ah, OK.

00:16:57.773 --> 00:16:58.200
Well, maybe a little.

00:16:58.801 --> 00:16:59.658
No, because you guys are trained.

00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:00.188
OK.

00:17:02.679 --> 00:17:06.519
Really analyze and plan your financial statements and cash flow.

00:17:07.125 --> 00:17:07.420
Cash flow.

00:17:08.101 --> 00:17:11.259
That's super important too, so you don't end up overleveraged,

00:17:11.662 --> 00:17:15.039
or get started at a bad time.

00:17:16.080 --> 00:17:20.000
I'm spending time on this with you because honestly, that's what saved me.

00:17:20.842 --> 00:17:23.519
And that's what kicked off everything that happened next.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:25.400
Basically, it became my Bible.

00:17:27.121 --> 00:17:31.259
So after I bought my properties,

00:17:31.502 --> 00:17:33.079
I kept checking all that to make sure I didn't mess up.

00:17:33.941 --> 00:17:35.980
Take every cost into account when making your decision.

00:17:36.801 --> 00:17:38.051
Sometimes, you know what we do?

00:17:38.071 --> 00:17:38.999
We play ostrich—just stick our heads in the sand.

00:17:40.680 --> 00:17:42.056
Want me to show you what being an ostrich looks like?

00:17:43.122 --> 00:17:43.294
Alright.

00:17:43.803 --> 00:17:44.779
I'll even show you physically,

00:17:44.900 --> 00:17:46.339
because apparently, I've been told I have a real talent for it.

00:17:47.622 --> 00:17:47.771
Okay.

00:17:48.468 --> 00:17:48.680
Here we go.

00:17:49.246 --> 00:17:49.838
Let's do the ostrich.

00:17:50.564 --> 00:17:51.295
So, what's the ostrich?

00:17:53.363 --> 00:17:54.579
Just so you know, my wife has never seen me do this.

00:17:54.859 --> 00:17:56.680
She's waiting for it, but I refused.

00:17:57.140 --> 00:17:57.248
Anyway.

00:17:58.500 --> 00:18:02.200
So, being an ostrich means telling yourself you've calculated this,

00:18:02.781 --> 00:18:05.579
you've calculated that, you've calculated this, but you still haven't calculated that one thing.

00:18:05.759 --> 00:18:06.380
But you think, it's fine, no big deal.

00:18:08.026 --> 00:18:08.599
That's what being an ostrich is.

00:18:10.204 --> 00:18:10.919
So, you need to calculate everything.

00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:13.720
Even the stuff you don't feel comfortable calculating, you have to do it.

00:18:14.682 --> 00:18:15.640
Don't skip that part,

00:18:15.700 --> 00:18:17.039
because that might be the part that costs you.

00:18:17.540 --> 00:18:19.140
Maybe not, but maybe it will.

00:18:19.803 --> 00:18:20.880
That's what happened to me.

00:18:22.141 --> 00:18:23.519
Keep control of your investments.

00:18:24.163 --> 00:18:25.019
That's also important to remember.

00:18:25.923 --> 00:18:27.980
Don't let yourself get influenced by salespeople.

00:18:29.082 --> 00:18:29.818
Analyze the numbers.

00:18:31.500 --> 00:18:35.118
Who today is getting influenced by people around them, and so on.

00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:36.409
Sometimes, we all tend to do that a little bit.

00:18:37.940 --> 00:18:41.098
Still, go and double-check what the so-called expert real estate agent tells you.

00:18:42.300 --> 00:18:43.740
Buy property where you live.

00:18:44.101 --> 00:18:46.559
It might sound silly, but honestly, I recommend you all do it.

00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:52.420
Honestly, we all have a time problem too, like I said before.

00:18:53.280 --> 00:18:57.299
If you start doing deals when you’re just getting started,

00:18:57.640 --> 00:19:00.640
and you’re an hour, two hours, three hours away from home,

00:19:01.086 --> 00:19:01.657
you might as well move.

00:19:03.321 --> 00:19:04.440
Seriously, just to save time.

00:19:06.122 --> 00:19:08.180
That’s actually one of the decisions some of you need to make.

00:19:10.722 --> 00:19:12.380
Who wants a net worth of 10 million?

00:19:15.025 --> 00:19:15.799
Sir, you’re not raising your hand.

00:19:16.463 --> 00:19:16.586
Are you?

00:19:16.689 --> 00:19:17.137
Okay, got it.

00:19:17.827 --> 00:19:18.355
She’s really…

00:19:18.579 --> 00:19:19.480
I need to see her myself.

00:19:21.086 --> 00:19:21.579
Let me tell you something.

00:19:22.221 --> 00:19:26.380
The goal with MDB is for you to have a net worth of 10 million.

00:19:27.359 --> 00:19:29.279
That’s the point of my talk.

00:19:30.461 --> 00:19:33.740
So I’m showing you all this so you can aim for that goal.

00:19:35.019 --> 00:19:42.119
But if you’re out in the middle of nowhere, and your biggest deals are a struggle,

00:19:43.221 --> 00:19:46.660
and you work your tail off, and in the end you’re left with 20,000 euros,

00:19:47.727 --> 00:19:48.279
it’s just not worth it.

00:19:48.561 --> 00:19:49.500
Or you’re really going to struggle.

00:19:50.580 --> 00:19:54.016
So for me, one of the decisions I made that was a real game changer,

00:19:55.580 --> 00:19:56.338
was going back to an English-speaking environment,

00:19:57.682 --> 00:20:01.160
which was huge for me—I decided to move.

00:20:02.205 --> 00:20:02.619
More than once.

00:20:03.619 --> 00:20:06.200
I left France, Nice, and moved to Geneva.

00:20:07.385 --> 00:20:07.693
Why?

00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:09.059
Because I was earning more money.

00:20:10.425 --> 00:20:11.240
So, I had more cash.

00:20:11.624 --> 00:20:12.279
Okay, I started buying.

00:20:13.160 --> 00:20:14.319
But I also lost money.

00:20:15.924 --> 00:20:16.999
Still, I kept reinvesting.

00:20:18.862 --> 00:20:21.000
And then, it started to snowball.

00:20:21.686 --> 00:20:21.880
Same thing.

00:20:22.561 --> 00:20:24.778
Once I’d built up a lot, I moved to Dubai.

00:20:25.500 --> 00:20:25.644
Wow!

00:20:26.241 --> 00:20:27.377
Are you sure, Jean-Germain, you really moved to Dubai?

00:20:27.519 --> 00:20:28.378
It's a bit intense there right now.

00:20:28.940 --> 00:20:29.480
Yeah, it's intense.

00:20:29.981 --> 00:20:31.720
But I'm there with my business partner, so it'll get better.

00:20:32.140 --> 00:20:33.519
But hey, we made a lot of money too.

00:20:34.221 --> 00:20:36.059
And the thing is, you can't control everything.

00:20:37.383 --> 00:20:39.019
Sometimes you just can't control what happens.

00:20:40.180 --> 00:20:42.000
So, the best advice I can give you,

00:20:42.981 --> 00:20:44.740
is to focus on what you can control.

00:20:45.702 --> 00:20:47.480
You can control where you live.

00:20:48.163 --> 00:20:50.200
You can check out your partners,

00:20:50.319 --> 00:20:52.900
or at least get a sense of who you're actually going to work with,

00:20:53.561 --> 00:20:54.218
who you'll be working with.

00:20:54.861 --> 00:20:58.039
You can check and see if you're in an area

00:20:58.463 --> 00:21:00.440
where, in the end, there really aren't that many opportunities

00:21:00.440 --> 00:21:02.400
to make money, or to make a lot of money.

00:21:04.349 --> 00:21:04.940
You're going to struggle.

00:21:05.442 --> 00:21:07.099
You'll take longer than others.

00:21:08.041 --> 00:21:09.759
Same thing for everyone who hasn't started yet,

00:21:09.779 --> 00:21:11.660
and hasn't done their first deals—I encourage you,

00:21:12.839 --> 00:21:13.599
imagine, you have a choice.

00:21:15.481 --> 00:21:17.419
You can choose to go into luxury,

00:21:18.561 --> 00:21:20.779
and potentially make hundreds of thousands of euros,

00:21:21.204 --> 00:21:21.659
maybe even millions.

00:21:22.340 --> 00:21:24.898
Or you can choose not to go into luxury.

00:21:27.182 --> 00:21:28.779
That doesn't mean you can't make money, especially,

00:21:28.819 --> 00:21:29.457
I know people,

00:21:29.800 --> 00:21:33.920
they do it with apartments, commercial, residential,

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:35.599
but they do it with a lot, a lot of volume.

00:21:36.102 --> 00:21:38.539
But when you're starting out, you have to keep that in mind.

00:21:39.881 --> 00:21:41.098
So, for everyone who hasn't started yet,

00:21:41.421 --> 00:21:44.759
I really encourage you to move forward on this.

00:21:45.361 --> 00:21:47.819
Oh man, I don't even have a minute per slide.

00:21:49.729 --> 00:21:50.059
Let's keep going.

00:21:53.261 --> 00:21:55.200
So, buying property where you live is super important.

00:21:55.480 --> 00:21:58.900
Set up investment rules with clear limits.

00:22:02.900 --> 00:22:05.319
If he won't drop his price by X, I walk away.

00:22:05.865 --> 00:22:06.660
You've set your own limit,

00:22:06.963 --> 00:22:08.160
so you don't get taken for a ride,

00:22:08.803 --> 00:22:10.480
based on the decisions you've made for yourself.

00:22:10.881 --> 00:22:12.420
Same thing when you're negotiating.

00:22:13.242 --> 00:22:13.739
Set your boundaries.

00:22:15.063 --> 00:22:16.740
Don't just trust people and what they say.

00:22:18.211 --> 00:22:18.460
It's tough.

00:22:18.980 --> 00:22:20.240
Sometimes we tend to trust people.

00:22:21.241 --> 00:22:22.220
But always double-check what people tell you.

00:22:23.401 --> 00:22:25.740
And especially check what they do compared to what they say.

00:22:26.766 --> 00:22:27.079
Really good...

00:22:27.161 --> 00:22:28.579
That's a life lesson right there, guys.

00:22:30.343 --> 00:22:32.039
Don't end up over-indebted.

00:22:32.782 --> 00:22:33.613
It happened to me, but...,

00:22:34.746 --> 00:22:35.819
So be careful about that too.

00:22:36.364 --> 00:22:37.119
Pay yourself first.

00:22:38.704 --> 00:22:39.640
And pay everyone else on time.

00:22:40.623 --> 00:22:42.119
It makes me smile because I used to be super detailed about this.

00:22:44.241 --> 00:22:47.359
Today, one of the best management tips I can give you,

00:22:48.143 --> 00:22:49.559
is that based on what you earn,

00:22:50.544 --> 00:22:54.440
you set up an automatic transfer straight to yourself.

00:22:56.102 --> 00:22:59.356
Who here doesn't have an automatic transfer set up for themselves?

00:23:00.579 --> 00:23:00.720
There you go.

00:23:01.201 --> 00:23:03.719
That's in action item number one.

00:23:04.663 --> 00:23:06.200
Because who's the most important person today?

00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:06.440
It's you.

00:23:07.682 --> 00:23:09.640
If there's one person who matters today, it's you.

00:23:10.462 --> 00:23:12.000
So, no matter how much you make,

00:23:12.321 --> 00:23:13.200
no matter what you used to do,

00:23:13.561 --> 00:23:14.740
whether you've done a marchand de biens deal,

00:23:14.839 --> 00:23:17.439
whether you're an employee, a student, or whatever,

00:23:18.767 --> 00:23:19.420
at the end of the month,

00:23:20.363 --> 00:23:22.559
the first person you pay before your rent,

00:23:23.368 --> 00:23:23.759
is yourself.

00:23:24.180 --> 00:23:25.700
But you need to have done your Money Management File,

00:23:25.920 --> 00:23:28.160
you need to understand it, and give yourself the exact amount.

00:23:28.582 --> 00:23:29.814
Because what happens next?

00:23:30.380 --> 00:23:32.900
Well, then you see what's left.

00:23:32.900 --> 00:23:35.859
That's what you'll use to decide which restaurant you go to.

00:23:37.023 --> 00:23:38.359
And for those who struggle to go out to eat,

00:23:39.203 --> 00:23:40.519
or who swipe their card too easily,

00:23:41.102 --> 00:23:41.819
stop using your cards.

00:23:42.882 --> 00:23:44.472
When you go out, just take cash, that's it.

00:23:46.079 --> 00:23:47.720
No, but that's really how I used to think back then.

00:23:48.882 --> 00:23:50.398
Because if you go out tomorrow with 100 bucks,

00:23:51.163 --> 00:23:51.876
or you go out with 500 bucks,

00:23:52.059 --> 00:23:53.000
you're not going to the same restaurant.

00:23:54.241 --> 00:23:56.579
All of this is good Money Management rules,

00:23:57.101 --> 00:23:59.799
Especially, again, for people who are just starting out.

00:24:00.181 --> 00:24:01.619
So, pay yourself first, that's super important,

00:24:02.022 --> 00:24:03.900
because that's also when you'll notice

00:24:04.223 --> 00:24:05.359
where there are gaps in your life.

00:24:05.700 --> 00:24:05.920
Trust me.

00:24:06.580 --> 00:24:08.079
Check your finances, evaluate the properties.

00:24:08.240 --> 00:24:08.859
Okay, I really need to speed up.

00:24:10.461 --> 00:24:13.978
Get advice from competent, qualified, reliable, and unbiased advisors.

00:24:14.723 --> 00:24:15.558
Here, we're unbiased.

00:24:17.060 --> 00:24:20.599
The project committee members are here to help you.

00:24:21.402 --> 00:24:23.680
Whether the deal goes through or not, it's for you.

00:24:23.842 --> 00:24:24.539
We're here to help you.

00:24:24.800 --> 00:24:30.099
So we're among the people who are qualified and better than others

00:24:30.382 --> 00:24:32.779
who might have a personal interest in the deal.

00:24:33.483 --> 00:24:34.638
It's worth checking that out.

00:24:35.221 --> 00:24:37.640
Look at the best structure and tax benefits when setting up the deal.

00:24:37.961 --> 00:24:40.118
Only invest in properties that actually make you money,

00:24:40.843 --> 00:24:41.960
that put cash in your pocket.

00:24:43.382 --> 00:24:47.880
If you're buying properties just to make an extra 100 bucks,

00:24:48.141 --> 00:24:51.299
or chasing something that won't really bring in much money,

00:24:51.380 --> 00:24:51.898
just don't do it.

00:24:52.740 --> 00:24:55.119
Because even if sometimes you get some nice deals and all,

00:24:55.779 --> 00:24:58.220
really focus on cash, deals, profits.

00:24:58.640 --> 00:24:59.338
That's super important.

00:25:00.720 --> 00:25:01.940
Diversify your portfolio, but not too much.

00:25:02.142 --> 00:25:03.096
Why did I give you lesson 15?

00:25:03.523 --> 00:25:04.398
Because some people say to themselves,

00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:08.516
"Yeah, but look, I bought a property and in the end..."

00:25:09.259 --> 00:25:10.359
Now, I know you're all marchand-de-biens here.

00:25:10.682 --> 00:25:12.057
But that's the idea, okay?

00:25:12.442 --> 00:25:15.118
The idea is to really keep in mind that you need to...

00:25:15.582 --> 00:25:17.739
Sometimes it's better to skip a deal that looks nice,

00:25:18.002 --> 00:25:19.000
if it doesn't bring in enough,

00:25:19.541 --> 00:25:22.000
so you can focus on a deal that's going to bring you at least...

00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:23.317
Personally, I'd aim for a 30% return.

00:25:24.803 --> 00:25:25.939
Anything under a 30% return,

00:25:26.701 --> 00:25:28.559
if you can't get that, it's not the right deal,

00:25:28.902 --> 00:25:30.818
you're not in the right place, maybe you need to move, maybe not,

00:25:31.862 --> 00:25:33.640
that's up to you, but you need to chase returns.

00:25:33.861 --> 00:25:35.357
Obviously, I'm talking about 30% over about 12 months.

00:25:36.740 --> 00:25:38.358
So diversify your portfolio, but not too much.

00:25:39.160 --> 00:25:41.680
If you go too far and diversify too much, you lose control,

00:25:41.819 --> 00:25:42.317
so be careful.

00:25:42.799 --> 00:25:43.859
And don't trust people blindly, like I said before.

00:25:44.066 --> 00:25:44.394
Okay, anyway.

00:25:45.166 --> 00:25:45.538
Mistakes.

00:25:45.799 --> 00:25:47.160
These are some other mistakes I made, but it's no big deal.

00:25:47.722 --> 00:25:48.259
Second story.

00:25:49.564 --> 00:25:50.318
There's a little video here.

00:25:51.585 --> 00:25:52.538
An electrical panel is expensive.

00:25:53.063 --> 00:25:54.237
An electrical panel costs 200€.

00:25:55.246 --> 00:25:55.717
This one costs 190€.

00:25:56.579 --> 00:25:57.859
By the way, where is the electrical panel?

00:26:00.903 --> 00:26:01.248
Where is it?

00:26:02.422 --> 00:26:04.037
Damn, is there seriously no electrical panel here or what?

00:26:06.599 --> 00:26:08.511
Yeah, well, we really lucked out here.

00:26:13.324 --> 00:26:15.839
We're really at the top in Danmas.

00:26:17.143 --> 00:26:18.079
With parking downstairs.

00:26:19.502 --> 00:26:22.059
Here, we knock down this wall and make it bigger.

00:26:24.122 --> 00:26:26.519
And here, we make a little gem, a small kitchen.

00:26:26.720 --> 00:26:28.211
And maybe the toilet will actually be visible here.

00:26:35.608 --> 00:26:36.099
That makes me smile.

00:26:36.721 --> 00:26:37.894
Do you guys like these kinds of videos or not?

00:26:41.279 --> 00:26:43.200
So coming from Miami, I got on the plane and thought,

00:26:43.362 --> 00:26:45.119
I absolutely have to find some record-breaking stuff.

00:26:45.240 --> 00:26:48.039
I think I spent 5 hours trying to find videos like this.

00:26:48.582 --> 00:26:49.299
I've got 2 or 3 coming up.

00:26:50.842 --> 00:26:52.435
November 18, 2011, that goes way back.

00:26:54.421 --> 00:26:56.059
I really did this especially for beginners.

00:26:56.701 --> 00:26:58.000
You can see what kind of mindset I was in.

00:26:58.500 --> 00:27:00.397
What did I repeat 25 times there that makes no sense?

00:27:00.806 --> 00:27:01.339
Electrical panel.

00:27:02.380 --> 00:27:02.443
Okay.

00:27:03.644 --> 00:27:05.000
My focus was really not in the right place.

00:27:07.020 --> 00:27:09.539
So here I am, at the same time as I have my apartment

00:27:11.202 --> 00:27:12.498
which would have lost me at least 20,000.

00:27:13.712 --> 00:27:13.776
Okay.

00:27:14.059 --> 00:27:15.000
But I haven't sold it yet.

00:27:15.961 --> 00:27:18.900
But then I find this opportunity, it's an inheritance deal.

00:27:19.884 --> 00:27:20.171
Total stroke of luck.

00:27:20.861 --> 00:27:22.759
I was spending all my time on listings and everything.

00:27:23.423 --> 00:27:25.359
I get there and I’m like, wait, there’s a price gap here.

00:27:25.946 --> 00:27:26.619
It was on Le Bon Coin.

00:27:27.263 --> 00:27:28.660
I contact the real estate agent.

00:27:28.881 --> 00:27:31.940
I stumble on an inheritance sale, and literally the next day I see it, I move fast.

00:27:32.559 --> 00:27:34.039
And this time, I know it’s a good opportunity,

00:27:34.261 --> 00:27:36.259
because I’d started writing down my lessons.

00:27:36.721 --> 00:27:38.420
And I told myself, if all the boxes are ticked, I’m good.

00:27:38.721 --> 00:27:39.778
It was in Anmas, I went to Geneva.

00:27:41.182 --> 00:27:44.097
It was an inheritance price, I think it was 89,000 euros.

00:27:44.759 --> 00:27:45.131
Anyway, whatever.

00:27:45.662 --> 00:27:47.500
With the marchand de biens deal and everything.

00:27:47.579 --> 00:27:49.880
Plus, I did something a little borderline back then.

00:27:50.622 --> 00:27:53.500
I put it as my main residence, sublet it under my name,

00:27:53.981 --> 00:27:55.980
made a quick 30,000 euros, net, whatever, don’t do that.

00:27:57.047 --> 00:27:57.539
Statute of limitations now.

00:27:57.539 --> 00:27:57.765
Alright?

00:27:59.402 --> 00:28:01.519
But it’s just to show you how creative you can get.

00:28:03.642 --> 00:28:05.012
Any creatives in the room?

00:28:06.000 --> 00:28:06.192
Okay.

00:28:07.804 --> 00:28:08.919
It's not amazing, but hey.

00:28:10.241 --> 00:28:11.679
So, this is my second deal.

00:28:12.201 --> 00:28:13.498
And so, what happens next?

00:28:14.148 --> 00:28:14.779
I talk to my mom.

00:28:16.680 --> 00:28:16.824
Okay?

00:28:16.864 --> 00:28:17.415
Yeah, that's good.

00:28:18.539 --> 00:28:19.711
Yeah mom, what do you think?

00:28:22.902 --> 00:28:25.498
And then she says, but what's going on with your first apartment?

00:28:27.126 --> 00:28:27.636
Don't worry!

00:28:33.040 --> 00:28:36.598
So basically, if I get this right, you want to buy a new apartment that looks pretty nasty, huh?

00:28:36.819 --> 00:28:38.539
So you're going to have to put some money into renovations.

00:28:40.040 --> 00:28:42.659
But your income—at that point, I was really kind of borderline.

00:28:43.622 --> 00:28:45.819
But the deal was really worth it, so I went for it anyway.

00:28:47.362 --> 00:28:51.960
And that's where, if you find good deals and you don't have the same problem, you move a lot faster.

00:28:52.660 --> 00:28:57.680
So actually, by doing my second deal, I made 30,000 euros, but in the end, it put me back over 10,000.

00:28:59.921 --> 00:29:00.003
Okay?

00:29:00.539 --> 00:29:11.180
So I could've gone straight ahead with the training, with the network, with advice from the project committee, with tips from all the people who really want to help me, and so on.

00:29:11.721 --> 00:29:14.299
I could've just started with 30,000 and then kept duplicating.

00:29:15.403 --> 00:29:16.660
So that's the story of the second deal.

00:29:19.079 --> 00:29:21.039
So yeah, I put in some nice little photos for you.

00:29:23.181 --> 00:29:24.460
Mindset shift number two.

00:29:26.365 --> 00:29:26.917
Good thing I...

00:29:27.601 --> 00:29:28.674
We're gonna need two hours!

00:29:32.483 --> 00:29:34.099
So, take action.

00:29:35.323 --> 00:29:36.119
Take action.

00:29:36.862 --> 00:29:39.140
Nothing will happen if you don't take action.

00:29:40.001 --> 00:29:42.999
But go for it, and make sure you get everything approved by the project committees and so on.

00:29:44.060 --> 00:29:45.359
So just ignore the doubts.

00:29:45.641 --> 00:29:47.920
A lot of the time, it's actually other people's doubts that get to you.

00:29:48.059 --> 00:29:53.059
Like, my mom—love her, respect her—but when it comes to financing,

00:29:54.040 --> 00:29:55.680
I'm really glad I did that deal, honestly.

00:29:56.621 --> 00:29:58.940
Seriously, I'm glad I did it, because it let me move on to something else.

00:29:59.340 --> 00:30:05.220
So don't listen to people who don't know, or who don't have the same bank account as the people who inspire you.

00:30:05.700 --> 00:30:05.920
You see what I mean?

00:30:05.920 --> 00:30:12.460
You know, the uncle, the aunt, the brother, the mom, the son, the cousin—always got something to say about everything.

00:30:13.343 --> 00:30:13.990
But the guy, he's...

00:30:15.124 --> 00:30:15.830
Like, for example...

00:30:17.124 --> 00:30:18.276
I'm not putting him down, but...

00:30:19.842 --> 00:30:21.700
No matter what he does in life, let's just say he's not giving great advice.

00:30:21.861 --> 00:30:22.397
Is that okay with you?

00:30:24.599 --> 00:30:28.960
So try to connect who’s giving you advice with how much they have in their bank account.

00:30:30.142 --> 00:30:31.539
Just to make rational decisions.

00:30:32.119 --> 00:30:32.872
You agree with that?

00:30:34.123 --> 00:30:35.420
If you're clapping, keep clapping.

00:30:35.903 --> 00:30:37.119
If you want to raise your hand, go ahead and do it.

00:30:39.201 --> 00:30:41.740
So, time versus money.

00:30:42.402 --> 00:30:43.720
Yeah, that's super important too.

00:30:44.621 --> 00:30:50.380
For my first apartment, I had to travel, you know, go check it out, it was in Le Canet, I lived in Geneva, all those round trips, flying EasyJet.

00:30:52.020 --> 00:30:52.986
Of course, not in...

00:30:53.006 --> 00:30:54.694
What do you call the people sitting right up front?

00:30:55.922 --> 00:30:56.751
Who here flies EasyJet?

00:30:56.771 --> 00:30:57.358
No one takes EasyJet?

00:30:58.304 --> 00:30:59.200
Anyway, you get what I mean.

00:30:59.701 --> 00:31:02.140
I'm all the way at the back of the plane, whatever, doesn't matter.

00:31:03.163 --> 00:31:03.920
Yeah, maybe.

00:31:06.142 --> 00:31:06.356
Anyway...

00:31:06.682 --> 00:31:08.960
So, what I'm trying to say is, I wasn't there.

00:31:09.059 --> 00:31:12.299
So honestly, I wasted a lot of time on something that didn't make me much money.

00:31:12.781 --> 00:31:13.797
But then, what happened?

00:31:14.721 --> 00:31:17.359
When I did my marchand de biens deal, I found the guy for the renovations,

00:31:17.760 --> 00:31:23.680
I basically pretended I had a master's in design, just by downloading some software,

00:31:24.340 --> 00:31:30.359
and I designed everything down to the last 10 cm, since the apartment wasn't that big—38 m² if I remember right—but I still managed to fit in a bedroom.

00:31:31.585 --> 00:31:33.759
I got super creative, worked on it until 2 a.m. and everything.

00:31:34.401 --> 00:31:37.157
I even pre-sold the 3D render for...

00:31:38.363 --> 00:31:40.400
Back then it was for renting, but it could've been for selling too.

00:31:41.440 --> 00:31:44.160
So yeah, we make up skills as we go, and that's actually great.

00:31:44.160 --> 00:31:46.979
But most of all, I spent 30 hours on it.

00:31:47.759 --> 00:31:50.640
I hired a contractor for the plumbing, another guy for something else.

00:31:50.960 --> 00:31:54.099
They were both highly recommended by the real estate agent who'd already done deals, etc.

00:31:54.621 --> 00:31:57.200
What I'm saying is, 30,000 euros for 30 hours of work, that's pretty good.

00:31:58.461 --> 00:32:00.019
And that's how I started thinking about it, actually.

00:32:00.700 --> 00:32:01.775
I thought, wow!

00:32:03.401 --> 00:32:06.819
That's when I realized I was going to be a multimillionaire.

00:32:07.346 --> 00:32:07.719
I already knew it.

00:32:08.520 --> 00:32:14.700
But it really boosted my goal, I just focused on that, I followed my whole list, my checklist and everything.

00:32:15.200 --> 00:32:18.019
So then, I was like, okay, cool, cool, let's do more.

00:32:18.501 --> 00:32:19.317
So, what happens next?

00:32:19.740 --> 00:32:23.598
I was working at a private bank, hated my job after the second day, just wanted to get out.

00:32:25.759 --> 00:32:32.038
But I was making good money, like 90,000 a year, with bonuses and all that stuff...

00:32:32.663 --> 00:32:34.659
I’m counting everything, the 401k, well, I don’t know what you call it here.

00:32:35.561 --> 00:32:36.816
Anyway, all the benefits, right?

00:32:38.185 --> 00:32:40.240
So then I thought, wait, there’s just too much money in real estate.

00:32:41.200 --> 00:32:41.955
So, what do I do?

00:32:42.643 --> 00:32:44.000
I tell myself, I’m going to be a real estate agent.

00:32:44.981 --> 00:32:46.619
On these deals, I might as well have them come to me.

00:32:47.383 --> 00:32:47.898
So, I switched.

00:32:49.181 --> 00:32:51.817
So, back then, who’s seen The Wolf of Wall Street?

00:32:52.769 --> 00:32:53.199
Okay, awesome.

00:32:54.541 --> 00:32:57.160
I went full 'Wolf of Wall Street' mode, but as a real estate agent.

00:32:57.944 --> 00:32:58.298
I started learning.

00:32:59.567 --> 00:33:00.200
And this, this is my office.

00:33:00.823 --> 00:33:02.059
My name’s written over there.

00:33:02.961 --> 00:33:05.680
The name was given to me at the bank, and I brought it over to my real estate gig.

00:33:06.359 --> 00:33:10.200
And that’s when I started, selling apartments.

00:33:11.101 --> 00:33:13.920
Then I started selling villas, because I thought, hang on, same effort.

00:33:14.701 --> 00:33:16.279
Apartment, villa—which one makes more money?

00:33:16.619 --> 00:33:17.220
Alright, let’s go for villas.

00:33:18.082 --> 00:33:19.720
Then I thought, wait, property development.

00:33:19.740 --> 00:33:20.169
Hmm, interesting.

00:33:21.559 --> 00:33:21.795
Property development.

00:33:22.261 --> 00:33:22.959
You're in the same place.

00:33:23.861 --> 00:33:25.819
Everyone comes to you when you move around.

00:33:26.641 --> 00:33:32.460
You can sell to 5 clients in 2 and a half hours if you do 30-minute meetings.

00:33:34.861 --> 00:33:39.039
Or in 5 hours if your meetings are an hour each, but you still saw 5 people in one afternoon.

00:33:40.740 --> 00:33:45.980
Because actually, what happened is I also discovered someone named Darren Hardy, who wrote 'The Compound Effect' or 'L'effet cumulé.'

00:33:46.039 --> 00:33:46.627
Who here has read 'L'effet cumulé'?

00:33:47.601 --> 00:33:50.519
Okay, everyone who hasn't, put this as an action item: buy 'L'effet cumulé.'

00:33:51.646 --> 00:33:52.039
It's for you.

00:33:53.141 --> 00:33:55.420
Time management is super important.

00:33:57.480 --> 00:34:01.180
So, once again, we're going to speed up, because remember, I have one minute per slide.

00:34:02.188 --> 00:34:02.619
So, it's tight.

00:34:03.461 --> 00:34:05.299
So basically, you get the lesson.

00:34:05.881 --> 00:34:12.759
"If I paid any attention to all the dumb shit people say, I would be just as miserable and broke as them."

00:34:13.641 --> 00:34:22.099
So yeah, you get it, if I listened to all the crap people say, I'd be just as miserable as they are.

00:34:22.280 --> 00:34:25.780
So, don't listen to people who don't know what they're talking about—that was mindset shift number 2.

00:34:26.159 --> 00:34:26.242
Okay!

00:34:26.262 --> 00:34:26.344
Hey!

00:34:30.402 --> 00:34:31.295
April 10, 2016.

00:34:32.121 --> 00:34:33.099
Alright, let me explain.

00:34:34.463 --> 00:34:35.639
When it came to time management, I was on top of it.

00:34:36.561 --> 00:34:38.679
Because I had an apartment, it was a studio.

00:34:39.222 --> 00:34:40.880
So, there was just a little kitchen on the left and all that.

00:34:41.021 --> 00:34:42.539
This is just to show you what I started out in, guys.

00:34:44.824 --> 00:34:45.498
I wanted to buy myself a Golf.

00:34:46.804 --> 00:34:47.599
But the Golf was more expensive.

00:34:49.581 --> 00:34:50.679
So yeah, it was a Polo.

00:34:52.862 --> 00:34:55.679
And I thought, come on, I'm not gonna drive around in a Polo.

00:34:58.322 --> 00:34:59.460
And then, something happened.

00:35:01.081 --> 00:35:02.858
Who here regrets buying a car too quickly?

00:35:03.920 --> 00:35:04.210
Raise your hand.

00:35:05.539 --> 00:35:05.753
Alright.

00:35:06.940 --> 00:35:10.579
Well, I told myself, damn, the Golf is faster,

00:35:10.940 --> 00:35:12.840
it's got more stuff, you know, back then.

00:35:13.923 --> 00:35:15.360
Honestly, I bought the Polo and kind of regretted it.

00:35:16.202 --> 00:35:20.059
But let's say, I did it smart—based on data.

00:35:21.164 --> 00:35:21.940
It was going to cost me less.

00:35:22.463 --> 00:35:23.260
The other one used more gas.

00:35:23.820 --> 00:35:24.713
It's silly, right?

00:35:25.199 --> 00:35:30.320
You start talking about gas, then insurance, then maintenance.

00:35:30.963 --> 00:35:32.639
But honestly, everything comes down to the details, guys.

00:35:33.822 --> 00:35:34.659
Especially for people just starting out.

00:35:35.239 --> 00:35:37.159
Of course, once you start making good money,

00:35:37.521 --> 00:35:40.519
if you start buying Ferraris, we'll talk about that later,

00:35:40.639 --> 00:35:42.099
because you do need to treat yourself sometimes.

00:35:42.380 --> 00:35:43.780
Don't worry, I've got slides for you too.

00:35:45.420 --> 00:35:48.679
But basically, yeah, my bed—sleep is important, right?

00:35:48.940 --> 00:35:51.079
So I wasn't about to buy a single bed, come on.

00:35:51.539 --> 00:35:52.059
You never know.

00:35:54.340 --> 00:35:54.900
So, there you go.

00:35:57.322 --> 00:35:59.757
That little desk you see on the right, that's where I did my 16 lessons and everything.

00:36:00.402 --> 00:36:02.539
The Buddha up there, my mom gave it to me, okay?

00:36:02.599 --> 00:36:03.798
Jean-Guyem Zenn, peace out.

00:36:05.322 --> 00:36:07.119
So yeah, I had everything right there, okay?

00:36:07.400 --> 00:36:09.440
Just wanted to give you an idea of my mindset back then.

00:36:10.300 --> 00:36:11.172
So, what's going on?

00:36:12.289 --> 00:36:12.353
Okay.

00:36:14.021 --> 00:36:15.097
Damn, Maud, you didn't blur me out.

00:36:15.981 --> 00:36:17.860
Alright, we've got a blue square on my head, no big deal.

00:36:19.262 --> 00:36:19.898
Story number 3.

00:36:21.300 --> 00:36:26.420
So now, this is gonna be my first deal in Switzerland.

00:36:26.721 --> 00:36:27.619
At this point, I'm a real estate agent.

00:36:29.141 --> 00:36:31.360
So, just to wrap up on the compound effect, I thought,

00:36:31.559 --> 00:36:34.099
there's money in development, so I'm gonna focus on property development,

00:36:34.179 --> 00:36:35.400
because that'll save me time.

00:36:35.639 --> 00:36:37.559
People come to me, you know, as a real estate agent, and so on.

00:36:38.302 --> 00:36:40.139
And then I started doing deals, right?

00:36:40.260 --> 00:36:41.817
I sold apartments, I sold villas at first, okay?

00:36:42.280 --> 00:36:45.860
Then I looked at my fellow agents' calendars.

00:36:45.980 --> 00:36:50.119
One's got a viewing here in the morning, another one's over there, another one somewhere else.

00:36:50.461 --> 00:36:51.438
Boom, day’s gone, done.

00:36:52.481 --> 00:36:52.550
Okay.

00:36:53.699 --> 00:36:53.871
Stupid.

00:36:55.201 --> 00:36:58.398
Why not just go to the same place, stack up meetings, and move forward like that?

00:36:58.581 --> 00:36:59.579
That's when I thought: development.

00:36:59.902 --> 00:37:00.920
Then I started looking at the numbers.

00:37:01.199 --> 00:37:01.465
Ok, I'm selling.

00:37:02.603 --> 00:37:03.539
That's when I really started making good money.

00:37:03.739 --> 00:37:04.786
So, I started out, 90,000, I was an employee.

00:37:07.219 --> 00:37:10.159
In Switzerland, I was on a 60,000 salary plus 10% commission.

00:37:10.740 --> 00:37:13.273
I would've loved to get 30% commission on 40, 50, 60, or 70 instead of my salary,

00:37:14.420 --> 00:37:14.739
but it's no big deal.

00:37:15.302 --> 00:37:15.659
That's just how it was.

00:37:15.780 --> 00:37:16.257
That's how they set it up.

00:37:17.521 --> 00:37:20.320
It wasn't a bad way to start, but after a while, I told him, look, I want more salary.

00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:21.460
I want it to change.

00:37:22.041 --> 00:37:27.438
Actually, I started making almost 90,000 the first year, then 125,000,

00:37:28.041 --> 00:37:29.208
and I ended up hitting 350,000 in a year.

00:37:31.601 --> 00:37:32.471
So that worked out to 1,750,000.

00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:36.699
The average for real estate agents was about 1 million.

00:37:38.141 --> 00:37:40.813
My goal was, I got a bonus if I did more than 650,000 or 750,000,

00:37:42.485 --> 00:37:43.480
and at 1 million, I got a bonus.

00:37:44.260 --> 00:37:47.539
And at one point, since I had a ton of deals, some developments, and so on,

00:37:47.960 --> 00:37:50.369
at one point, I had the chance to bring in 1,750,000 for the company.

00:37:53.481 --> 00:37:56.539
And I got a cut of that, with my salary and everything, okay?

00:37:56.539 --> 00:38:00.072
I asked him, so what kind of bonus do I get if I hit 1,250,000, 1,500,000, 1,750,000, or even 2 million?

00:38:02.402 --> 00:38:06.179
I totally blew up their pay structure, so they had to change it.

00:38:06.659 --> 00:38:10.119
Just to let you know, and at the end, I told him, I want more salary, and so on,

00:38:10.300 --> 00:38:11.119
because there's real money in the commission.

00:38:11.440 --> 00:38:13.780
Just so you know, I stayed a real estate agent for 5 years.

00:38:15.501 --> 00:38:17.719
Another mistake you should never make, no matter what you do in life,

00:38:18.061 --> 00:38:20.619
If you decide to commit, you need to commit for 5 years.

00:38:22.721 --> 00:38:25.898
For those of you just starting out, thinking you’ll make it in marchand de biens in a year,

00:38:27.222 --> 00:38:29.880
or in two years, that you’ll hit your goals—honestly, you can leave right now.

00:38:32.762 --> 00:38:34.858
Well, at least you’re showing some respect for the presentation, I appreciate that.

00:38:37.621 --> 00:38:38.670
It’s five years, guys.

00:38:38.690 --> 00:38:39.818
It’s five years, it’s a five-year commitment.

00:38:40.141 --> 00:38:42.820
That’s five years where you need to come here every year.

00:38:43.601 --> 00:38:46.159
You need to network, because things will happen, breakthroughs and all that.

00:38:46.440 --> 00:38:48.239
So, I’m trying to save you time with my stories.

00:38:48.579 --> 00:38:49.630
That’s why I’m sharing them with you.

00:38:49.650 --> 00:38:50.440
That’s why I’m taking the time.

00:38:51.101 --> 00:38:54.898
So, I’m thinking, okay, I’m studying, and I’m like, damn, there’s money in real estate, alright, great.

00:38:55.420 --> 00:38:56.980
And that’s when I start making financial plans.

00:38:57.521 --> 00:39:02.617
So, I sell a really big real estate project, and I’m thinking, damn, if I were the developer, how much would I have made?

00:39:03.099 --> 00:39:04.266
Wow!

00:39:04.327 --> 00:39:05.795
And that’s when I start interviewing them.

00:39:05.815 --> 00:39:06.440
So, I invite him over.

00:39:06.800 --> 00:39:08.300
So here he is in the photo, of course, I blurred him out.

00:39:09.661 --> 00:39:10.286
It’s April 10, 2016.

00:39:10.306 --> 00:39:12.000
No, it’s not the Geneva studio.

00:39:13.260 --> 00:39:15.074
There’s the time, but it doesn’t matter.

00:39:15.114 --> 00:39:15.719
We’re in a nightclub here.

00:39:17.019 --> 00:39:20.907
We’re in a nightclub.

00:39:20.949 --> 00:39:21.956
So, what’s going on here?

00:39:21.976 --> 00:39:22.440
I don’t remember anymore.

00:39:22.639 --> 00:39:23.472
But hey, it was a fun night.

00:39:23.492 --> 00:39:23.775
It was cool.

00:39:24.240 --> 00:39:26.059
So, here's another tip for you.

00:39:27.460 --> 00:39:30.860
People in your area who are making money, big money,

00:39:31.021 --> 00:39:33.920
when you get the chance to meet them or work for them,

00:39:34.501 --> 00:39:37.920
or help them make a lot of money, invite them out to lunch.

00:39:39.440 --> 00:39:42.500
Write this down, action number 3: invite the rich guy.

00:39:44.400 --> 00:39:48.320
So you go with them, and you start to discover things,

00:39:48.681 --> 00:39:49.838
and you start asking them questions.

00:39:50.079 --> 00:39:51.675
"Hey, by the way, why do you do it like that?

00:39:51.735 --> 00:39:52.099
How do you do it?

00:39:52.222 --> 00:39:53.099
And that's when you start to get it.

00:39:53.800 --> 00:39:57.980
And thanks to him, I learned a way to structure deals.

00:39:58.760 --> 00:39:59.476
That's worth a million dollars.

00:40:01.043 --> 00:40:02.639
It made me a ton of money.

00:40:03.126 --> 00:40:03.659
That's what taught me.

00:40:03.920 --> 00:40:05.119
And I realized, actually, you need to be a developer.

00:40:06.081 --> 00:40:06.619
Or, well, a promoter.

00:40:06.699 --> 00:40:08.820
In what I was doing, in one of my strategies, that was it.

00:40:09.503 --> 00:40:10.760
Because honestly, you were making too much money.

00:40:12.121 --> 00:40:15.579
So I started my first deal.

00:40:16.061 --> 00:40:17.416
Not bad, huh, the house?

00:40:18.224 --> 00:40:19.358
Still not a Geneva studio, though.

00:40:19.420 --> 00:40:20.539
There's a mistake.

00:40:20.860 --> 00:40:21.418
No big deal.

00:40:23.583 --> 00:40:25.719
This is in Colonge-Belle-Rive.

00:40:26.664 --> 00:40:27.215
Colonge-Belle-Rive?

00:40:27.420 --> 00:40:28.617
Anyone here know it?

00:40:29.106 --> 00:40:29.659
Colonge-Belle-Rive.

00:40:30.485 --> 00:40:31.217
It's a nice place, right?

00:40:31.744 --> 00:40:32.717
Pretty cool, huh?

00:40:32.860 --> 00:40:32.947
Alright.

00:40:33.565 --> 00:40:34.280
We had a plot of land.

00:40:35.541 --> 00:40:38.079
So we split it up to build three nice houses.

00:40:38.521 --> 00:40:38.851
So there you go.

00:40:39.920 --> 00:40:42.539
And that's how I did my first deal,

00:40:43.784 --> 00:40:44.938
where I was a real estate agent.

00:40:45.282 --> 00:40:45.920
I found the land.

00:40:46.362 --> 00:40:51.079
Instead of selling the land to people looking for a house,

00:40:51.903 --> 00:40:53.239
or people who want to build on it,

00:40:54.019 --> 00:40:55.880
I thought, why not go talk to investors instead.

00:40:56.320 --> 00:40:59.400
So I started changing my pitch as a real estate agent.

00:41:01.382 --> 00:41:02.719
Everything I’m telling you stays here, okay?

00:41:03.804 --> 00:41:04.778
For you, your property, alright.

00:41:06.766 --> 00:41:07.358
So what's my point?

00:41:07.440 --> 00:41:08.880
I was a real estate agent and I thought, okay,

00:41:09.842 --> 00:41:11.079
now I'm only going to look for investors.

00:41:11.239 --> 00:41:14.380
So with this land, I was still working in the client's best interest.

00:41:14.702 --> 00:41:15.869
What did the client want?

00:41:15.889 --> 00:41:16.898
What does the client want?

00:41:16.918 --> 00:41:17.179
The seller.

00:41:17.722 --> 00:41:18.630
He wants as much money as possible.

00:41:18.811 --> 00:41:19.295
Right?

00:41:19.981 --> 00:41:24.179
So tomorrow, if a developer can put down 20 or 30% more,

00:41:24.726 --> 00:41:25.260
the guy's happy.

00:41:25.539 --> 00:41:26.719
That's how I locked in some deals.

00:41:27.320 --> 00:41:29.478
So I wasn't going to investors to build those houses, etc.

00:41:30.820 --> 00:41:35.940
And so, instead of doing what most people do,

00:41:36.601 --> 00:41:38.539
like real estate agents who just send you random files,

00:41:38.659 --> 00:41:39.036
total nonsense.

00:41:39.701 --> 00:41:41.478
No, my file was like a data room, seriously.

00:41:41.539 --> 00:41:44.280
Here's the location, here's how much I can buy it for,

00:41:44.739 --> 00:41:46.179
here's how much I think I can negotiate it down to,

00:41:46.800 --> 00:41:50.280
and here's what I knew about the developer.

00:41:51.161 --> 00:41:53.179
So here's what the construction costs will be.

00:41:53.460 --> 00:41:54.719
Here's the architect, here's all the details.

00:41:55.081 --> 00:41:56.960
The guy just had a financial plan, he just needed to fund the start,

00:41:56.980 --> 00:41:57.579
because I didn't have any money.

00:41:58.280 --> 00:42:00.617
Who here doesn't have money and is struggling to find deals?

00:42:01.019 --> 00:42:02.152
This is for you, OK?

00:42:03.342 --> 00:42:04.168
You good?

00:42:04.188 --> 00:42:05.659
Did I spend money to do all that?

00:42:05.880 --> 00:42:07.030
Yeah, just a little to invite the guy.

00:42:07.050 --> 00:42:07.998
And let's relax, okay?

00:42:08.583 --> 00:42:10.396
No money means no money, you agree or not?

00:42:10.820 --> 00:42:10.963
Huh?

00:42:10.983 --> 00:42:11.065
Alright.

00:42:12.422 --> 00:42:14.958
When you tell me, 'I have no money,' you're still here, aren't you!

00:42:15.260 --> 00:42:15.382
Right?

00:42:15.402 --> 00:42:15.485
Okay.

00:42:21.182 --> 00:42:22.918
So, what I'm saying is...

00:42:24.121 --> 00:42:24.746
Where was Jean?

00:42:24.766 --> 00:42:25.873
Who was following along?

00:42:25.893 --> 00:42:26.155
No one?

00:42:26.175 --> 00:42:26.257
Alright.

00:42:28.260 --> 00:42:28.695
Data room.

00:42:29.304 --> 00:42:29.896
Yeah, data room.

00:42:30.081 --> 00:42:30.780
Exactly.

00:42:31.039 --> 00:42:35.699
So instead of just sending the info like that, I put together a file for him, basically, the guy tells me...

00:42:36.061 --> 00:42:37.039
Actually, he didn't have any questions at all.

00:42:37.902 --> 00:42:38.559
Here are the sale prices.

00:42:40.920 --> 00:42:42.139
Minimum, base, target.

00:42:42.599 --> 00:42:44.719
Here's how you'll do it, basically, how much you'll make.

00:42:46.760 --> 00:42:46.842
Okay?

00:42:46.862 --> 00:42:46.945
Alright.

00:42:48.603 --> 00:42:49.556
I tell him, 'Do you want the project?

00:42:49.880 --> 00:42:50.996
Yeah, it looks interesting, yeah.

00:42:51.117 --> 00:42:51.260
Okay.

00:42:52.103 --> 00:42:52.655
I want 10% of the project.

00:42:54.920 --> 00:42:55.043
What?

00:42:56.182 --> 00:42:57.579
Do you want a cut of the profits?

00:42:57.679 --> 00:42:59.815
I told him, "No worries, if you don't want it, it's fine, no problem."

00:43:01.599 --> 00:43:04.494
"No, no, don't worry, it's all good, go ahead, we can talk, etc."

00:43:06.021 --> 00:43:08.960
Guys, creating value is what's going to make you a lot of money.

00:43:09.980 --> 00:43:15.014
You need to make a ton of money starting with nothing—walou, nada, zilch, whatever language you want.

00:43:17.121 --> 00:43:19.679
So, 10% was basically nothing extra back then.

00:43:20.760 --> 00:43:22.820
And I think it turned into a negotiation.

00:43:22.840 --> 00:43:28.480
He gave me like 100,000 or 110,000 Swiss francs, a flat amount, whatever, no questions asked.

00:43:29.005 --> 00:43:29.478
I accepted.

00:43:30.322 --> 00:43:31.820
But hey, that was still my first six-figure deal.

00:43:32.900 --> 00:43:33.853
That's pretty cool!

00:43:34.806 --> 00:43:35.110
Thanks!

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:36.085
Alright.

00:43:40.820 --> 00:43:44.217
So, on top of that, what else happened?

00:43:45.463 --> 00:43:47.280
I sold the land, took my commission.

00:43:48.862 --> 00:43:50.440
I negotiated exclusive rights to sell the three houses.

00:43:51.246 --> 00:43:51.960
I sold all three houses.

00:43:52.945 --> 00:43:55.320
I got the project bonus.

00:43:59.123 --> 00:43:59.938
Mindset shift number 3.

00:44:00.784 --> 00:44:01.255
March 7, 2013.

00:44:01.880 --> 00:44:03.480
Making money without putting in money is possible.

00:44:04.041 --> 00:44:05.699
The guy you can't see in the back, he was the investor.

00:44:06.599 --> 00:44:08.898
So I started changing my mindset and shifting

00:44:09.302 --> 00:44:11.019
the people I wanted to talk to on the phone,

00:44:11.722 --> 00:44:12.980
and the kind of people I wanted around me.

00:44:13.163 --> 00:44:14.099
And that's when I started telling people,

00:44:15.485 --> 00:44:17.280
"I'm in real estate, want to make some money?

00:44:17.461 --> 00:44:18.454
Let's do some property development, etc."

00:44:19.282 --> 00:44:21.219
And eventually, someone introduced me to someone

00:44:21.523 --> 00:44:23.059
who actually ended up being one of my investors.

00:44:23.422 --> 00:44:24.079
He ended up investing.

00:44:24.800 --> 00:44:26.559
So, story number 4.

00:44:28.125 --> 00:44:29.139
The scaling focus.

00:44:30.202 --> 00:44:33.039
With just one partner, we did four deals.

00:44:33.681 --> 00:44:34.635
So, what did I think?

00:44:36.344 --> 00:44:37.559
We made good money, he was happy too.

00:44:37.902 --> 00:44:38.920
Don't worry, I know how to count.

00:44:39.965 --> 00:44:40.070
Scro.

00:44:42.523 --> 00:44:43.840
So, I have another plot.

00:44:45.443 --> 00:44:46.032
What do I do?

00:44:47.065 --> 00:44:47.320
Loyalty.

00:44:47.913 --> 00:44:48.039
Cool.

00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:49.059
I go see him.

00:44:49.860 --> 00:44:49.945
Okay?

00:44:50.384 --> 00:44:50.900
So, I have a plot.

00:44:51.402 --> 00:44:52.519
This time, it's a plot with a house on it,

00:44:52.820 --> 00:44:54.159
but the house has a really big yard.

00:44:55.041 --> 00:45:00.119
The seller, a cop, super nice guy, tells me,

00:45:00.219 --> 00:45:02.237
"Well, actually, I want to sell my land for..."

00:45:02.500 --> 00:45:03.032
He's ready, no stress.

00:45:03.641 --> 00:45:05.460
So basically, he wants as much money as possible.

00:45:06.159 --> 00:45:06.827
Alright?

00:45:08.019 --> 00:45:12.500
I tell him, "Don't worry, I'm the one who's going to bring you the biggest check

00:45:13.583 --> 00:45:14.619
to buy your land."

00:45:15.260 --> 00:45:17.371
I want exclusivity for a month, two months, whatever.

00:45:19.322 --> 00:45:19.487
Okay?

00:45:20.121 --> 00:45:20.748
Not in a hurry, this guy?

00:45:22.181 --> 00:45:23.719
You know, sometimes you can negotiate things like that,

00:45:24.306 --> 00:45:24.940
that cost you nothing,

00:45:26.121 --> 00:45:27.920
but give you options in your life.

00:45:28.726 --> 00:45:29.175
So, what's the deal?

00:45:29.561 --> 00:45:32.195
It's just telling him, "Give me two months, three months."

00:45:33.221 --> 00:45:34.378
Worst case, you ask for six months,

00:45:34.882 --> 00:45:35.980
he negotiates you down to three months,

00:45:36.907 --> 00:45:38.000
you end up with four or five months,

00:45:38.403 --> 00:45:39.199
you've got four months ahead of you,

00:45:39.523 --> 00:45:40.458
and you make something happen,

00:45:40.920 --> 00:45:43.900
find an investor for this project in those four months.

00:45:45.282 --> 00:45:48.380
Not like, "Yeah, okay, two, three, four, eight, ten,

00:45:49.141 --> 00:45:50.552
starfish, starfish, zero."

00:45:51.480 --> 00:45:52.119
I call that starfish.

00:45:53.043 --> 00:45:53.559
When you go here,

00:45:54.744 --> 00:45:56.938
and you go there,

00:45:58.184 --> 00:45:59.059
I'm doing this so you get what I mean,

00:45:59.239 --> 00:45:59.452
okay?

00:45:59.599 --> 00:46:00.452
It's a bit annoying, but...

00:46:01.063 --> 00:46:02.018
Alright, what's going on?

00:46:02.387 --> 00:46:02.820
I didn't move.

00:46:04.605 --> 00:46:05.460
But if you only hit here,

00:46:07.405 --> 00:46:08.300
and you do it several times,

00:46:08.820 --> 00:46:10.119
it's like chopping at a tree.

00:46:11.800 --> 00:46:11.903
Okay?

00:46:13.246 --> 00:46:13.992
Who chops wood here?

00:46:15.967 --> 00:46:16.360
Chop some wood.

00:46:16.722 --> 00:46:18.119
Alright, we can chop wood.

00:46:19.822 --> 00:46:20.777
Who has a fireplace here?

00:46:21.922 --> 00:46:22.873
Okay, who has firewood?

00:46:23.460 --> 00:46:24.313
Alright, you need to chop wood properly.

00:46:24.659 --> 00:46:25.434
So, yeah.

00:46:26.902 --> 00:46:29.480
You chop wood on a log.

00:46:30.141 --> 00:46:31.579
Imagine, you made one cut.

00:46:33.005 --> 00:46:33.940
Oh hey, let me go try the other one.

00:46:35.208 --> 00:46:37.960
Oh hey.

00:46:39.800 --> 00:46:41.719
No, but here, I'm doing this on purpose so you can picture it,

00:46:41.900 --> 00:46:42.400
because it's important.

00:46:43.985 --> 00:46:44.208
Okay?

00:46:44.230 --> 00:46:44.719
Games of Thrones.

00:46:46.786 --> 00:46:47.699
I didn't cut anything there.

00:46:48.668 --> 00:46:49.980
That's what a lot of people do.

00:46:51.099 --> 00:46:52.217
That's focus.

00:46:53.722 --> 00:46:55.918
So, you take your best tree.

00:46:58.202 --> 00:47:01.139
You put a fence around the tree.

00:47:02.079 --> 00:47:03.579
You add a little gate.

00:47:11.146 --> 00:47:11.579
And then, it falls.

00:47:13.260 --> 00:47:16.599
And right there, that's the difference between everyone here in the room

00:47:17.300 --> 00:47:19.460
and the people in Marchand de Bien who didn't come to the event.

00:47:19.719 --> 00:47:20.398
Give yourselves a round of applause.

00:47:22.480 --> 00:47:22.800
Applause.

00:47:27.842 --> 00:47:29.099
Because you are the ones making the difference.

00:47:29.768 --> 00:47:30.139
Not them.

00:47:30.699 --> 00:47:31.115
You.

00:47:32.400 --> 00:47:34.019
For understanding these things.

00:47:35.099 --> 00:47:37.818
So, are you still with me?

00:47:38.141 --> 00:47:38.576
Okay.

00:47:38.840 --> 00:47:39.697
Are you still following?

00:47:39.800 --> 00:47:39.862
Okay.

00:47:40.420 --> 00:47:41.456
Do you like stories or not?

00:47:41.960 --> 00:47:42.175
Okay.

00:47:42.519 --> 00:47:42.773
Let's keep going.

00:47:45.179 --> 00:47:46.516
Honestly, I swear, I have no idea how we're going to do this.

00:47:46.840 --> 00:47:47.280
Anyway, it's funny.

00:47:48.440 --> 00:47:48.568
So,

00:47:55.384 --> 00:47:56.135
They're the ones who want it, you know.

00:47:56.155 --> 00:47:56.380
Not me.

00:47:57.583 --> 00:47:58.159
The client is king, right?

00:47:58.561 --> 00:47:59.420
See, I warned you.

00:47:59.641 --> 00:48:00.380
You didn't want to give me two hours.

00:48:01.086 --> 00:48:01.358
Now you deal with it.

00:48:02.202 --> 00:48:03.440
Next time, put it in the survey.

00:48:04.141 --> 00:48:07.157
If you see we're running out of time, just say, 'Jean-Guy needs two or three hours.'

00:48:07.961 --> 00:48:08.710
So, uh, anyway.

00:48:11.943 --> 00:48:13.320
Yeah, so, I'm on my land.

00:48:13.684 --> 00:48:14.219
Mr. So-and-so.

00:48:14.882 --> 00:48:15.619
There you go, don't worry.

