00:58:37.423 --> 00:58:38.260
That's the takeaway.

00:58:41.262 --> 00:58:43.000
We stay focused, that was before.

00:58:43.382 --> 00:58:44.099
Now, what's happening?

00:58:44.240 --> 00:58:46.940
We're focusing our investment efforts on one deal

00:58:47.222 --> 00:58:48.599
where we've done our homework so well.

00:58:49.822 --> 00:58:53.139
We know the market inside out—resale prices, all that stuff, you name it.

00:58:53.822 --> 00:58:56.400
We know the only real risk is,

00:58:56.561 --> 00:58:57.692
can I afford the loan payments?

00:58:58.682 --> 00:58:59.418
Yes, I can cover the loan.

00:58:59.802 --> 00:59:00.719
Can I live there if I need to?

00:59:00.903 --> 00:59:01.418
Yes, I could live there.

00:59:02.143 --> 00:59:03.320
Basically, we do this so well,

00:59:04.023 --> 00:59:06.099
that honestly, yeah, we took a risk,

00:59:06.563 --> 00:59:08.559
because I put a big chunk of my cash into it,

00:59:09.340 --> 00:59:15.239
because in Dubai, you had to show up with 30 or 40% equity for the property.

00:59:15.320 --> 00:59:16.958
So I bought it for 4.8 million dirhams,

00:59:17.623 --> 00:59:18.820
divide that by 4 to get the amount in euros.

00:59:18.820 --> 00:59:22.097
I put in 1.6, and I sold it for 11.8.

00:59:22.780 --> 00:59:23.389
Alright?

00:59:26.943 --> 00:59:29.480
And actually, when I wanted to sell, someone told me

00:59:30.061 --> 00:59:34.356
"I'll buy it from you, break the contract, I'll give you the 10% and buy it for more."

00:59:35.340 --> 00:59:36.373
And actually, when the seller…

00:59:37.123 --> 00:59:38.115
Oh yeah, damn!

00:59:39.802 --> 00:59:40.673
Story within the story!

00:59:44.820 --> 00:59:46.597
They show up, and they're…

00:59:47.161 --> 00:59:51.518
The dad—it's a couple with three little girls.

00:59:55.043 --> 00:59:56.259
And honestly, I started to get attached.

00:59:57.983 --> 00:59:59.380
Some of you have already sold properties,

00:59:59.559 --> 01:00:01.480
and you're just so happy with the people who are buying

01:00:01.722 --> 01:00:03.420
that you just want to sell to them and no one else,

01:00:03.480 --> 01:00:04.320
and it's not just about the money.

01:00:04.902 --> 01:00:05.940
Yeah, that's part of business too.

01:00:06.500 --> 01:00:10.280
See, someone offered me to break the contract for them so I could make more money.

01:00:10.740 --> 01:00:12.139
But they were invested, I felt...

01:00:12.322 --> 01:00:13.039
They felt at home...

01:00:13.684 --> 01:00:15.420
The little girl felt at home, she picked out her room,

01:00:15.840 --> 01:00:17.559
the tiniest one, like, 'I'm going to put my stuff here.'

01:00:18.302 --> 01:00:20.619
And honestly, I never even thought about breaking the contract.

01:00:20.739 --> 01:00:21.019
Why not?

01:00:21.101 --> 01:00:21.574
Because he was struggling to...

01:00:22.001 --> 01:00:24.199
He needed three months, four months, five, even six more months.

01:00:24.679 --> 01:00:26.159
Because actually, when I was supposed to sell that house,

01:00:26.422 --> 01:00:27.840
I found the house I wanted to buy next.

01:00:28.628 --> 01:00:28.978
And I missed out on it.

01:00:29.599 --> 01:00:30.440
Because they weren't ready.

01:00:31.527 --> 01:00:31.980
That hurt a bit.

01:00:32.760 --> 01:00:35.351
So I call them back, and I'm like, 'Okay, that's nice, but now what are we doing here?'

01:00:37.820 --> 01:00:40.340
Yeah, story within a story within a story.

01:00:41.119 --> 01:00:41.226
Laughter

01:00:44.101 --> 01:00:45.960
Technically, we can't transfer ownership.

01:00:47.239 --> 01:00:49.619
Technically, I take out a loan, he fronts me the money.

01:00:51.420 --> 01:00:55.199
So I can buy—not that house, because I lost it—another house.

01:00:58.143 --> 01:00:59.940
So I end up owning both houses.

01:01:00.601 --> 01:01:03.380
We did all the contracts and everything, set my conditions, but I still bought my house.

01:01:04.141 --> 01:01:07.599
And actually, when they're ready, that's when we transfer ownership.

01:01:07.820 --> 01:01:10.699
It was possible to do it that way and set it up by contract.

01:01:11.079 --> 01:01:11.880
So we were able to pull it off.

01:01:13.284 --> 01:01:14.219
That still let me lock things down.

01:01:14.420 --> 01:01:16.378
On top of that, when I told him I missed out on my house,

01:01:16.740 --> 01:01:18.039
I asked him for 500,000 dirhams more.

01:01:19.483 --> 01:01:20.280
Well, that covers the fees, you know.

01:01:21.605 --> 01:01:22.438
A little over 120,000 bucks.

01:01:23.061 --> 01:01:23.550
Just like that!

01:01:24.423 --> 01:01:25.356
Power of negotiation!

01:01:26.360 --> 01:01:27.659
Damn, we're going to see him this afternoon.

01:01:28.559 --> 01:01:32.079
I'm supposed to talk to you about mindset, but this is just so you get it,

01:01:32.179 --> 01:01:32.817
because everything's connected, really.

01:01:33.719 --> 01:01:37.300
So yeah, I didn't sell to the other guy.

01:01:38.240 --> 01:01:41.340
I explained to him, logically, that I still lost the house I wanted,

01:01:41.380 --> 01:01:42.878
and that he needed to get moving.

01:01:43.882 --> 01:01:45.139
I told him, I want a bit more.

01:01:45.360 --> 01:01:46.289
He said, okay, you know what?

01:01:46.329 --> 01:01:47.599
That's fair, that's right, that's reasonable.

01:01:47.820 --> 01:01:48.650
Okay, why not?

01:01:48.670 --> 01:01:49.440
I'll give you the difference.

01:01:50.019 --> 01:01:50.679
I didn't resell.

01:01:50.920 --> 01:01:54.780
Turns out, while I needed to grab my phone and call everyone

01:01:54.961 --> 01:01:56.376
to try and raise 30 million dollars in 70,

01:01:57.541 --> 01:02:00.860
well, actually, he's the one who introduced me to his boss,

01:02:01.443 --> 01:02:02.679
who ended up investing 30 million dollars.

01:02:04.081 --> 01:02:07.260
Karma—when you do things right, it pays off.

01:02:07.420 --> 01:02:08.599
Sometimes, you don’t realize it right away.

01:02:10.744 --> 01:02:11.936
You see the story within the story?

01:02:12.822 --> 01:02:14.894
Who else thinks it’s cool to do good and have it come back to you?

01:02:15.702 --> 01:02:17.382
Okay.

01:02:19.963 --> 01:02:22.960
If I hadn’t sold to him, I would’ve been a jerk.

01:02:24.181 --> 01:02:27.300
If I’d tried to get a bit more, I would’ve missed out on this deal.

01:02:27.920 --> 01:02:28.253
Potentially.

01:02:28.923 --> 01:02:29.391
Are you following me?

01:02:30.221 --> 01:02:32.719
So, always, you know, take the right steps.

01:02:32.860 --> 01:02:34.496
We really need to speed up, so I’m going to go faster, okay?

01:02:36.782 --> 01:02:38.699
There are three parts to this presentation.

01:02:39.121 --> 01:02:41.400
This is story 6 out of 8 in the first part.

01:02:41.965 --> 01:02:42.659
We’ve got 27 minutes left.

01:02:44.500 --> 01:02:47.039
So, yeah, this is just to show you the idea of scaling.

01:02:47.199 --> 01:02:49.219
This was the very first villa we did.

01:02:49.820 --> 01:02:53.079
Alright, I’ll move on, you get it—the first opportunity came along, and so on.

01:02:53.219 --> 01:02:53.340
Anyway.

01:02:54.161 --> 01:02:56.579
Mindset shift number 7: building relationships pays off.

01:02:57.019 --> 01:03:00.840
We raised 30 million dollars, we built relationships, trust, and scaled up.

01:03:01.079 --> 01:03:05.619
Here I am with Guillaume, we’re having dinner to celebrate the partnership.

01:03:06.240 --> 01:03:08.199
On the right, that was the lawyer.

01:03:08.402 --> 01:03:09.219
We fought like crazy, seriously.

01:03:09.699 --> 01:03:13.780
Thirty million dollar contract, he’s putting up all the money, he even gets the property, and so on.

01:03:14.181 --> 01:03:16.719
It was back-and-forth negotiations for two, three weeks.

01:03:17.222 --> 01:03:19.059
But we got there and still closed the deals.

01:03:19.320 --> 01:03:22.056
Today, story 8, we're at the 46th villa as of March 31st.

01:03:23.282 --> 01:03:26.878
We've deployed 327 million dollars, bought 45 properties, and made 31 exits.

01:03:27.960 --> 01:03:31.539
So far, we've distributed over 80 million dollars in profits that we've collected,

01:03:31.983 --> 01:03:33.599
along with our investors and our network.

01:03:34.460 --> 01:03:37.958
If we sell at market value, total profits would be 191.

01:03:39.041 --> 01:03:43.619
So minus the 80, that means we still have 111 million dollars in profits to go after.

01:03:44.139 --> 01:03:44.498
Alright?

01:03:44.621 --> 01:03:45.336
That was for the 30.

01:03:45.802 --> 01:03:46.719
We've sold one more since then.

01:03:47.201 --> 01:03:49.719
If you ask, Jean Guillaume, what's the return on investment you've achieved so far?

01:03:49.739 --> 01:03:55.039
On average, it's 69% across the 30 deals, in under 18 months on average.

01:03:56.663 --> 01:03:58.134
For the whole portfolio, it's 56%.

01:03:59.682 --> 01:04:04.079
And what we aim for in our business is to make between 30 and 50% per deal.

01:04:04.099 --> 01:04:09.099
And investors will make between 60 and 70%, depending on their investment ticket.

01:04:09.382 --> 01:04:11.199
And we take the difference with the platform.

01:04:11.340 --> 01:04:13.199
We have 4 villas we're keeping for ourselves for now.

01:04:13.360 --> 01:04:15.672
And we have 11 villas—well, now 10—up for sale.

01:04:18.452 --> 01:04:18.619
That's it.

01:04:19.880 --> 01:04:20.134
OK.

01:04:23.920 --> 01:04:24.235
Thanks.

01:04:25.201 --> 01:04:29.079
Again, it's really a team effort, it's sweat and hard work.

01:04:29.563 --> 01:04:30.039
It's been 5 years.

01:04:30.460 --> 01:04:33.231
Since 2020, that's how we started the first ones.

01:04:35.380 --> 01:04:36.715
So, it's not something you do all at once.

01:04:37.400 --> 01:04:38.079
But we focused.

01:04:39.061 --> 01:04:41.318
To give you an idea, we focused on Jumeir Island—we bought 35 properties there.

01:04:42.079 --> 01:04:44.219
We're the biggest developers in that community.

01:04:44.360 --> 01:04:46.260
And now, we're branching out into other communities.

01:04:46.380 --> 01:04:48.440
So, what's mindset shift number 8?

01:04:48.440 --> 01:04:50.039
It's that you have to organize your growth.

01:04:50.679 --> 01:04:54.239
So today, you've got the founders, but also a managing director, project manager,

01:04:54.539 --> 01:04:57.280
site engineers, site managers, architects, and so on.

01:04:57.440 --> 01:05:00.699
And actually, what we did in Dubai, we're doing with Maxime too, just like Yann said.

01:05:00.900 --> 01:05:03.219
And we're still building that up and teaming up with people.

01:05:03.701 --> 01:05:07.159
I guarantee you, if you're in this room—who's hungry here?

01:05:08.304 --> 01:05:09.157
Who's really hungry?

01:05:10.146 --> 01:05:10.211
OK.

01:05:11.599 --> 01:05:15.318
Honestly, if you didn't raise your hand right away, you're already not qualified.

01:05:15.561 --> 01:05:17.295
You see, it's like, I ask who's hungry?

01:05:17.315 --> 01:05:17.860
And you're just sitting there.

01:05:19.563 --> 01:05:20.619
Then I ask who's really hungry?

01:05:22.083 --> 01:05:23.235
You’re just not hungry enough.

01:05:23.275 --> 01:05:23.639
Just chill.

01:05:24.659 --> 01:05:25.500
Or maybe you didn't get it.

01:05:27.041 --> 01:05:29.900
Those of you who are hungry, my friends, you're going to partner up with us.

01:05:31.025 --> 01:05:31.579
Some of you, anyway.

01:05:32.005 --> 01:05:32.699
We're going to fund you.

01:05:33.463 --> 01:05:34.440
You'll find partners.

01:05:34.963 --> 01:05:37.000
We're going to help you go out and get millions of dollars.

01:05:37.521 --> 01:05:41.840
Because if you think this is the end, no, this is just the beginning.

01:05:42.849 --> 01:05:43.280
It's just the beginning.

01:05:44.166 --> 01:05:44.739
We haven't done anything yet.

01:05:45.186 --> 01:05:46.119
And I say that with total humility.

01:05:46.380 --> 01:05:46.932
You know why?

01:05:47.260 --> 01:05:48.597
Because right now, we're hungry.

01:05:49.146 --> 01:05:49.400
Really hungry.

01:05:49.699 --> 01:05:50.516
And we want to help a lot of people.

01:05:51.041 --> 01:05:51.639
And that's exactly what we're doing.

01:05:51.920 --> 01:05:55.000
And that's why I came all the way from Miami, to bring you this message

01:05:55.581 --> 01:06:01.280
because it's important to help open your eyes, your ears, your heart, and your gut,

01:06:01.722 --> 01:06:05.400
and everything else you need so you can make the right decisions,

01:06:06.001 --> 01:06:08.840
do your first deal, then keep doing more deals,

01:06:09.320 --> 01:06:11.780
stay focused, and avoid all the damn mistakes we've made.

01:06:12.123 --> 01:06:14.260
And if you think you've seen the best video, it's coming.

01:06:15.668 --> 01:06:16.139
It's coming.

01:06:16.867 --> 01:06:17.320
We're moving fast.

01:06:18.179 --> 01:06:26.039
So, bottom line, at the end of the day, as a marchand-de-biens, if we keep it simple, you wear four main hats.

01:06:26.782 --> 01:06:28.139
First hat: finding the deal.

01:06:28.643 --> 01:06:29.139
Everything starts with the deal.

01:06:30.141 --> 01:06:34.739
Try to note this right now: if you're a deal hunter, you're good at finding deals.

01:06:35.465 --> 01:06:36.077
That's one focus.

01:06:36.561 --> 01:06:38.054
Second focus: raising funds.

01:06:39.041 --> 01:06:39.927
Who's putting up the money?

01:06:39.947 --> 01:06:40.833
Who's going to raise the funds?

01:06:40.853 --> 01:06:41.557
Who's going to handle that?

01:06:42.041 --> 01:06:44.739
Third focus: who's the guy managing the renovations?

01:06:46.487 --> 01:06:46.940
The operation.

01:06:47.862 --> 01:06:50.599
No matter what you're doing—marchand, redevelopment, splitting up properties—

01:06:51.021 --> 01:06:53.619
the person who's going to manage, let's say, the deal, the project, the execution.

01:06:54.260 --> 01:06:56.336
Number four: who's handling the sale?

01:06:56.942 --> 01:06:58.139
Until we've sold, we haven't cashed in.

01:06:58.740 --> 01:07:03.440
For us, to keep it simple, it's Guillaume who finds the deals,

01:07:04.246 --> 01:07:05.639
and through the whole network we've built,

01:07:05.719 --> 01:07:08.900
because now we have a network of over 250 brokers bringing us deals.

01:07:09.260 --> 01:07:11.719
When you focus on a market, you know what happens?

01:07:11.719 --> 01:07:13.119
People come to you—the deals, you don't even have to look for them anymore.

01:07:14.402 --> 01:07:15.619
And you know your market so well,

01:07:16.760 --> 01:07:19.980
that you don't even need to go see it to know if you want to buy or not.

01:07:20.239 --> 01:07:21.019
Because you know everything.

01:07:21.320 --> 01:07:25.500
You just need to know the sale price, suggest the price we can negotiate,

01:07:25.920 --> 01:07:27.878
what's the size, if there have been any extensions or not,

01:07:28.764 --> 01:07:30.079
the size of the land, and that's it.

01:07:30.501 --> 01:07:32.239
We handle everything else, don't worry.

01:07:32.360 --> 01:07:34.719
You give us those three pieces of info, we tell you yes, no, the price.

01:07:35.126 --> 01:07:35.291
Bam!

01:07:35.724 --> 01:07:36.480
Decisions get made fast.

01:07:37.219 --> 01:07:37.800
So focus.

01:07:38.199 --> 01:07:40.920
I hope you got it, especially you newbies out there.

01:07:41.382 --> 01:07:42.018
Figure out your plan.

01:07:42.500 --> 01:07:46.260
Spend more time deciding if you're actually going to move or not.

01:07:47.059 --> 01:07:47.900
I'm totally serious.

01:07:49.041 --> 01:07:50.059
Spend more time figuring that out.

01:07:50.440 --> 01:07:52.619
Spend more time negotiating with your family,

01:07:52.960 --> 01:07:54.539
because maybe you're married, you have kids, all that.

01:07:55.199 --> 01:07:56.719
Don't just come home and say,

01:07:56.739 --> 01:07:59.480
"Jean-Guillaume said we're moving, that's it, we're off to Abu Dhabi."

01:07:59.579 --> 01:08:00.954
No, no, that's not what I'm saying, okay?

01:08:02.800 --> 01:08:03.898
Don't put words in my mouth.

01:08:04.320 --> 01:08:06.920
I'm just saying, some of you should really ask yourselves,

01:08:06.940 --> 01:08:08.737
"Damn, where I live is the middle of nowhere.

01:08:08.960 --> 01:08:09.264
I love it, really.

01:08:09.284 --> 01:08:09.489
I do love it.

01:08:10.840 --> 01:08:13.380
But for five years, we're going to go over there and make money.

01:08:14.420 --> 01:08:15.759
And after that, we'll see, we'll decide.

01:08:16.342 --> 01:08:17.359
Originally, we were supposed to stay five years.

01:08:17.460 --> 01:08:19.059
We've been here seven years, and I have no plans to leave.

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:20.300
I'm telling you.

01:08:20.943 --> 01:08:21.619
But hey, we're here, obviously.

01:08:21.819 --> 01:08:23.140
But in France and all, it's no problem.

01:08:23.520 --> 01:08:25.359
And we're still doing deals in France, in Annecy and so on.

01:08:25.739 --> 01:08:28.479
But just to say, back then, we saw an opportunity there.

01:08:28.962 --> 01:08:29.560
We jumped on it.

01:08:29.640 --> 01:08:30.880
Now, we want to expand internationally.

01:08:31.622 --> 01:08:33.079
We want to do more deals in Switzerland.

01:08:33.199 --> 01:08:35.020
By the way, I'd love to talk to everyone who's in Switzerland.

01:08:35.360 --> 01:08:37.399
Come see me, I'll be there tonight, or whenever, I don't know.

01:08:37.420 --> 01:08:39.197
Come see me, I've got a deal, I've got a deal, I've got a deal.

01:08:39.823 --> 01:08:41.159
We've got people who want to get in on the Swiss market.

01:08:41.480 --> 01:08:42.699
We've got people who want to get in on the French market.

01:08:43.060 --> 01:08:45.000
We're raising funds right now, but others will tell you more about that.

01:08:45.761 --> 01:08:47.599
If I start talking about that now, we're done for.

01:08:47.720 --> 01:08:51.060
This is just to show you that we want to grow on a global scale.

01:08:51.199 --> 01:08:53.458
There are opportunities everywhere, whether it's in France, Douban, wherever.

01:08:53.961 --> 01:08:58.920
But in your area in France, you need to find the spot where you'll make money, or even more.

01:08:59.340 --> 01:09:02.600
So some of you, especially the newbies, you need to ask yourself,

01:09:02.841 --> 01:09:04.893
is it more about luxury?

01:09:04.912 --> 01:09:06.118
Is it more about penthouses?

01:09:06.260 --> 01:09:09.840
Am I just going to do penthouses on one avenue, because on that avenue,

01:09:09.920 --> 01:09:11.800
you know, there are some avenues where you make a ton of money,

01:09:12.140 --> 01:09:13.573
but the street right behind, it's minus 50%.

01:09:14.921 --> 01:09:15.840
So focus on that avenue.

01:09:16.842 --> 01:09:18.000
You need to become an expert on that avenue.

01:09:18.320 --> 01:09:20.119
Me? You know what, I'm an expert on that avenue.

01:09:20.940 --> 01:09:23.399
And the deals will come to you, because you'll be talking about it to everyone.

01:09:23.460 --> 01:09:24.653
People will say, "Oh, you're an expert?"

01:09:24.672 --> 01:09:25.037
What have you done?

01:09:25.341 --> 01:09:26.319
"I've done stopper and s'est-topper."

01:09:26.742 --> 01:09:28.354
And don't worry, I'm going to do ten more, I've got a pipeline and everything.

01:09:29.224 --> 01:09:29.469
Why?

01:09:29.489 --> 01:09:29.734
What's up?

01:09:31.144 --> 01:09:31.899
And that's how you do it.

01:09:32.100 --> 01:09:34.100
You build it—focus and niche are super important.

01:09:35.125 --> 01:09:36.000
So yeah, that's what I was saying.

01:09:36.523 --> 01:09:37.938
So I'm in charge of fundraising.

01:09:38.859 --> 01:09:38.988
Jean.

01:09:39.520 --> 01:09:41.698
So you might say, 'There's Guillaume, there's Jean, there's Jean-Guillaume.'

01:09:41.840 --> 01:09:43.439
That's not on purpose, just so you know.

01:09:44.860 --> 01:09:49.180
Jean, our managing director, ex-BNP Paribas, 20 years, ex-JLL,

01:09:50.240 --> 01:09:51.859
huge expertise—he only handles the renovation work.

01:09:52.421 --> 01:09:55.840
And I oversee the network of sellers,

01:09:56.301 --> 01:10:00.420
where we also have our own brokerage company, Bonaparte, in France,

01:10:00.539 --> 01:10:03.418
but we also set up Bonaparte in Dubai to control the sales, and so on.

01:10:04.025 --> 01:10:05.319
So we hired our own brokers and everything,

01:10:05.601 --> 01:10:06.898
and we work with a network of over 200 brokers

01:10:07.640 --> 01:10:11.439
that we've built up over the last 5 years,

01:10:11.621 --> 01:10:13.319
so they help us source properties, sell, and so on.

01:10:13.579 --> 01:10:15.500
So you see, everyone has their own role.

01:10:15.619 --> 01:10:18.500
Now, when you're starting out, you're alone, it's tough, you have to do everything.

01:10:18.920 --> 01:10:21.019
You have to find the property, do the GLL, all that stuff—it's hard.

01:10:21.400 --> 01:10:24.479
So try to find a partner, maybe from your second deal or even the first,

01:10:24.742 --> 01:10:26.399
if you really have a great deal,

01:10:26.822 --> 01:10:30.119
but remember, to scale up—that's why this is mindset shift number 8,

01:10:30.841 --> 01:10:33.356
for those who are more advanced—some have done up to 25 deals, and so on.

01:10:34.119 --> 01:10:37.760
If you want to do bigger deals, you need to define your role more clearly.

01:10:38.260 --> 01:10:39.488
Alright?

01:10:39.509 --> 01:10:40.073
Good.

01:10:40.113 --> 01:10:41.000
Okay, let's move on quickly.

01:10:41.423 --> 01:10:43.177
Did you like the 10 laws of success, those stories or not?

01:10:44.739 --> 01:10:45.648
Okay!

01:10:45.688 --> 01:10:45.788
Alright.

01:10:45.809 --> 01:10:45.930
Let's go.

01:10:48.782 --> 01:10:51.078
For the 10 laws of success, just take pictures,

01:10:51.442 --> 01:10:53.194
and listen to me at the same time, it'll go fast, okay?

01:10:53.215 --> 01:10:53.475
Sound good?

01:10:54.422 --> 01:10:57.140
So, that's exactly my point.

01:10:58.081 --> 01:10:59.752
Who do you want to be?

01:10:59.774 --> 01:11:00.640
Who do you want to become?

01:11:00.881 --> 01:11:03.140
This guy here, Arnold Schwarzenegger, he was in Austria.

01:11:03.860 --> 01:11:07.298
He saw a Mister Olympia magazine and said, I want to be Mister Olympia.

01:11:08.162 --> 01:11:10.859
He focused only on that, and he became Mister Olympia.

01:11:11.841 --> 01:11:13.439
Then, he said, I want to do movies.

01:11:13.621 --> 01:11:14.479
But come on, your accent is terrible.

01:11:15.280 --> 01:11:18.479
No one understands what you're saying, it's impossible, that's just how it is, etc.

01:11:18.862 --> 01:11:20.220
You're way too muscular anyway, it won't work, and so on.

01:11:20.743 --> 01:11:21.140
You don't get it.

01:11:21.600 --> 01:11:25.619
The guy said, I'll be the highest paid in movies.

01:11:25.720 --> 01:11:25.905
Boom!

01:11:25.926 --> 01:11:26.238
He did it.

01:11:26.761 --> 01:11:28.800
Ah, I'm going into politics, because I care about people.

01:11:29.483 --> 01:11:30.279
I love people, I want to help them.

01:11:31.181 --> 01:11:32.939
He couldn't be President of the Republic because he was born in Austria.

01:11:33.820 --> 01:11:35.939
But he did become Governor of California.

01:11:36.283 --> 01:11:36.408
Bam!

01:11:36.429 --> 01:11:36.719
He did it.

01:11:37.462 --> 01:11:39.180
Three decisions, his whole life.

01:11:39.703 --> 01:11:40.979
You can have several lives, ladies and gentlemen.

01:11:42.667 --> 01:11:43.319
I'm totally serious.

01:11:44.041 --> 01:11:47.337
Think about your life, no matter how old you are, as...

01:11:52.761 --> 01:11:53.759
Phones on mute, please.

01:11:54.261 --> 01:11:55.179
You forgot to mention that at the entrance.

01:11:57.101 --> 01:11:58.859
That's super important for the next two days.

01:12:00.462 --> 01:12:03.600
You might get a call, text, whatever, do something.

01:12:03.760 --> 01:12:07.399
That's exactly when you should've been listening, and you'll miss the thing that could've made you x10.

01:12:08.420 --> 01:12:08.918
It's happened to me.

01:12:09.300 --> 01:12:09.859
It happens to everyone.

01:12:10.283 --> 01:12:10.779
It happens every year.

01:12:11.350 --> 01:12:11.880
There's no way to know.

01:12:12.060 --> 01:12:12.418
It's intangible.

01:12:12.539 --> 01:12:13.577
How could we possibly track that?

01:12:15.779 --> 01:12:18.139
So, forget your phone, be here, be focused.

01:12:19.701 --> 01:12:24.000
We're here together because every detail matters, every story matters, every spark.

01:12:24.382 --> 01:12:25.219
Oh damn, if only I'd known...

01:12:25.301 --> 01:12:25.530
Ah but...

01:12:25.740 --> 01:12:26.150
Okay?

01:12:26.563 --> 01:12:26.876
With me.

01:12:28.079 --> 01:12:29.460
So, you can live several different lives.

01:12:31.500 --> 01:12:34.179
Picture your life in chunks of at least 5 years, or even 20 years.

01:12:34.421 --> 01:12:35.479
Me, I'm on a 20-year ride right now.

01:12:36.779 --> 01:12:37.114
20 years.

01:12:37.819 --> 01:12:38.572
I've already got 10 years behind me.

01:12:39.340 --> 01:12:40.079
And there are 10 more years ahead.

01:12:41.039 --> 01:12:43.779
And in 10 years, I’ve got my goals, my plans, all that stuff too.

01:12:45.061 --> 01:12:46.279
Today, you can decide...

01:12:46.819 --> 01:12:48.619
I don’t know, some of you—because we only get one life, guys.

01:12:49.342 --> 01:12:50.399
We only get one fucking life.

01:12:51.430 --> 01:12:51.559
Okay?

01:12:51.720 --> 01:12:54.079
If you believe in reincarnation and all that, I might even be one of you.

01:12:54.324 --> 01:12:54.979
That’s not even the point.

01:12:55.501 --> 01:12:57.899
Right now, today, whether we have one life or many,

01:12:58.840 --> 01:13:03.720
let’s just try to do the best for ourselves, for our family, for our kids,

01:13:04.199 --> 01:13:08.800
for our grandkids, and be the person who really makes a change.

01:13:09.841 --> 01:13:12.420
I'm not doing some cheap motivational speaking here.

01:13:13.001 --> 01:13:16.739
I'm talking about real, internal commitment—that’s why you’re here,

01:13:17.542 --> 01:13:19.319
so that afterwards you’ll go after so much more.

01:13:20.041 --> 01:13:21.960
We’re just here to open doors and spark things, that’s it.

01:13:21.979 --> 01:13:24.119
You’re the ones who’ll do the work, you’re the ones who’ll make it all happen.

01:13:24.699 --> 01:13:27.560
But what I mean is, let’s say you told yourself in life,

01:13:27.979 --> 01:13:32.579
like, I want—I don’t know—I want to be a doctor, and I want to be a marchand de biens (property trader),

01:13:32.961 --> 01:13:34.757
and then after that, I want to do naturopathy.

01:13:35.180 --> 01:13:35.304
Okay?

01:13:35.323 --> 01:13:35.716
Whatever.

01:13:36.447 --> 01:13:36.800
It's your life.

01:13:37.541 --> 01:13:39.260
No one can judge your success or what you want to do.

01:13:40.081 --> 01:13:41.000
So go for it.

01:13:41.480 --> 01:13:43.880
You were a doctor for a year, maybe now it's time to be a marchand de biens

01:13:43.880 --> 01:13:45.759
for another part of the year, and then you can be a naturopath.

01:13:46.579 --> 01:13:48.659
Honestly, it's way nicer to be a naturopath, enjoy yourself,

01:13:48.720 --> 01:13:51.880
do whatever you want with your life, travel, whatever,

01:13:52.140 --> 01:13:53.872
when you've got a bit of cash, right?

01:13:53.912 --> 01:13:54.033
Okay?

01:13:56.320 --> 01:13:59.139
Me, I wanted to be a movie actor at first.

01:14:01.421 --> 01:14:03.939
Then I wanted to be a doctor, three years of studying.

01:14:04.621 --> 01:14:07.720
My grandfather was a doctor, surgeon, obstetrician, gynecologist.

01:14:07.900 --> 01:14:08.680
He advised my dad against it.

01:14:09.881 --> 01:14:10.931
I thought, how many years is that?

01:14:10.952 --> 01:14:11.578
Ten years?

01:14:11.618 --> 01:14:11.779
No way.

01:14:13.523 --> 01:14:14.300
Second, I wanted to join the army.

01:14:15.159 --> 01:14:16.439
I was going to join the army because I like people.

01:14:17.264 --> 01:14:18.000
I wanted to protect them, and so on.

01:14:18.239 --> 01:14:19.579
When the World Trade Center attacks happened,

01:14:20.701 --> 01:14:23.479
it really shook me, and I went to see them.

01:14:23.943 --> 01:14:24.819
They welcomed me like cattle.

01:14:25.302 --> 01:14:25.800
I didn't enjoy it.

01:14:25.899 --> 01:14:27.800
I thought, I'll always have someone telling me what to do and all that.

01:14:28.506 --> 01:14:29.760
It just didn't fit my personality.

01:14:29.859 --> 01:14:30.899
So I told myself, in the end, let's not do that.

01:14:31.000 --> 01:14:32.800
Let's try to help people in a different way.

01:14:33.863 --> 01:14:35.340
So I figured, business is what's left for me.

01:14:35.680 --> 01:14:36.418
I ended up in business.

01:14:36.979 --> 01:14:38.819
That's how my decision process went.

01:14:39.802 --> 01:14:40.899
And maybe one day, I'll do movies.

01:14:41.622 --> 01:14:43.239
I think maybe I've got something to offer.

01:14:43.904 --> 01:14:44.578
At least a little show.

01:14:45.921 --> 01:14:46.779
But I told myself,

01:14:46.819 --> 01:14:48.960
it'll always be easier to do business,

01:14:49.180 --> 01:14:49.576
make money.

01:14:49.859 --> 01:14:51.439
And then, if I want to blow some cash

01:14:51.863 --> 01:14:54.060
to put on a show, a movie, something like that,

01:14:54.320 --> 01:14:54.878
it'll be easier.

01:14:55.121 --> 01:14:57.220
Instead of struggling like crazy,

01:14:57.260 --> 01:14:58.698
and I can't do both at the same time.

01:14:59.582 --> 01:15:01.800
So, if you have goals you can work on today,

01:15:02.042 --> 01:15:03.760
life is short, but at the same time, it's long,

01:15:03.840 --> 01:15:04.189
it comes in stages.

01:15:05.502 --> 01:15:08.039
And your success depends on those stages, on your moves.

01:15:09.662 --> 01:15:10.755
Maud, I don't give a damn!

01:15:12.260 --> 01:15:12.408
So,

01:15:14.882 --> 01:15:16.300
Who do you really want to be? That's super important.

01:15:16.561 --> 01:15:18.600
Ask yourself that question in the world of property flipping.

01:15:19.939 --> 01:15:20.153
Deal finder,

01:15:21.323 --> 01:15:21.932
fundraiser,

01:15:23.020 --> 01:15:23.439
operator,

01:15:24.220 --> 01:15:24.390
seller.

01:15:24.903 --> 01:15:25.559
Basically, to keep it simple.

01:15:26.542 --> 01:15:27.279
Total responsibility.

01:15:27.681 --> 01:15:28.559
Alright, in this room,

01:15:29.322 --> 01:15:33.260
if anyone here still feels like a victim

01:15:35.425 --> 01:15:36.479
when it comes to ownership,

01:15:36.780 --> 01:15:37.899
we're going to have to leave that behind.

01:15:38.826 --> 01:15:39.779
I've been there myself,

01:15:40.908 --> 01:15:41.539
being a victim,

01:15:42.764 --> 01:15:44.340
just sitting there blaming others,

01:15:45.025 --> 01:15:45.819
making excuses,

01:15:46.961 --> 01:15:48.359
waiting for someone to come help me,

01:15:49.243 --> 01:15:49.838
complaining.

01:15:50.081 --> 01:15:51.180
"Oh, but you see, for me,

01:15:51.280 --> 01:15:52.775
you're different, whatever, all that stuff."

01:15:54.407 --> 01:15:55.039
We're all the same.

01:15:57.141 --> 01:15:59.300
We all need to eat, drink, do our thing.

01:15:59.541 --> 01:16:00.798
You think your wife or your husband

01:16:02.242 --> 01:16:04.115
is the worst in the world?

01:16:06.145 --> 01:16:07.018
You think you're the only one

01:16:07.323 --> 01:16:08.179
who have problems in your relationship,

01:16:08.539 --> 01:16:09.435
with your kids, with your business partners?

01:16:09.801 --> 01:16:10.729
No, it's everyone, 100%.

01:16:12.382 --> 01:16:13.640
So, victim mentality,

01:16:14.042 --> 01:16:14.779
that's going to crash you into a wall.

01:16:15.663 --> 01:16:16.699
You take responsibility,

01:16:17.524 --> 01:16:18.600
you make the right decisions,

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:20.079
you take action,

01:16:20.685 --> 01:16:21.439
and you'll get results.

01:16:21.863 --> 01:16:22.460
It's really that simple.

01:16:23.943 --> 01:16:25.679
The moment you decide to say

01:16:25.760 --> 01:16:27.359
"Now, that's it,

01:16:27.943 --> 01:16:29.340
I'm not a damn victim

01:16:29.887 --> 01:16:30.720
of my circumstances anymore",

01:16:30.962 --> 01:16:32.774
and you say, "I own it, bam!"

01:16:33.701 --> 01:16:34.699
You take responsibility,

01:16:35.300 --> 01:16:37.859
you lost 20,000 euros,

01:16:37.960 --> 01:16:38.936
you won't lose them again!

01:16:40.786 --> 01:16:41.659
I could've just said, "Oh, no,

01:16:41.699 --> 01:16:42.386
real estate doesn't work for me!"

01:16:49.242 --> 01:16:50.935
"Then plus 30,000 right after, boom, plus 10,000!"

01:16:51.560 --> 01:16:52.399
And wait, let me tell you...

01:16:52.663 --> 01:16:53.458
You think I never lost anything?

01:16:53.520 --> 01:16:54.140
I'll show you in a minute.

01:16:55.282 --> 01:16:55.967
Come on, let's go!

01:16:55.988 --> 01:16:56.451
Discipline!

01:16:57.726 --> 01:16:57.871
Oh?

01:16:58.140 --> 01:16:59.030
Well yeah, why not?

01:17:00.761 --> 01:17:02.176
Oh, you—I'm gonna crush you!

01:17:03.342 --> 01:17:03.948
I'm gonna crush you!

01:17:07.800 --> 01:17:08.511
Wow, that's heavy!

01:17:09.020 --> 01:17:10.899
Oh, that's...

01:17:10.899 --> 01:17:11.078
Poof!

01:17:11.140 --> 01:17:12.519
She's calling me from over there, I don't even know if I should say...

01:17:12.560 --> 01:17:12.938
Karma, karma!

01:17:13.404 --> 01:17:14.150
I think that's karma!

01:17:15.527 --> 01:17:15.960
Actually, I...

01:17:16.061 --> 01:17:17.000
Wait, to be honest with you,

01:17:17.282 --> 01:17:18.439
I put it on silent,

01:17:18.862 --> 01:17:19.693
but do you have favorites?

01:17:20.381 --> 01:17:21.331
When your favorites call you?

01:17:22.481 --> 01:17:23.051
Well, it still rings!

01:17:24.981 --> 01:17:26.595
So, I'm gonna take her off my favorites!

01:17:27.841 --> 01:17:27.970
Uh...

01:17:28.221 --> 01:17:28.993
There, happy now?

01:17:30.641 --> 01:17:31.880
Okay, 12 minutes, I have no idea how we're gonna do this.

01:17:32.100 --> 01:17:33.398
I'm telling you, get your backstage ready!

01:17:33.682 --> 01:17:34.172
Get organized!

01:17:34.884 --> 01:17:35.935
So, discipline!

01:17:37.220 --> 01:17:38.859
Mindset without discipline is useless!

01:17:39.001 --> 01:17:40.359
Alright, I won't dwell on that, you get it!

01:17:40.484 --> 01:17:41.020
Grow!

01:17:41.141 --> 01:17:41.917
Personal development...

01:17:42.182 --> 01:17:42.774
Take pictures!

01:17:43.161 --> 01:17:45.037
Personal development is a huge time saver!

01:17:45.359 --> 01:17:48.239
The better you get, the less time it takes to reach your goals!

01:17:48.300 --> 01:17:48.889
Brian Tracy, it's true!

01:17:49.761 --> 01:17:50.960
Today, you're working on personal development,

01:17:51.181 --> 01:17:52.420
if you're not, you should start—why?

01:17:52.420 --> 01:17:54.079
You need to read books, you need to learn!

01:17:54.202 --> 01:17:55.060
You're right to do this,

01:17:55.280 --> 01:17:57.439
but honestly, this should be the bare minimum every year,

01:17:57.641 --> 01:17:58.359
you need to be here, get together,

01:17:58.742 --> 01:17:59.998
see how others have made progress,

01:18:00.322 --> 01:18:01.576
shared, etc., for years now!

01:18:02.041 --> 01:18:04.359
Because, well, you're going to save time!

01:18:05.079 --> 01:18:06.039
Remember when I asked,

01:18:06.140 --> 01:18:07.153
who has a problem with time?

01:18:08.103 --> 01:18:10.338
Everyone has a freaking problem with time!

01:18:11.006 --> 01:18:12.039
When you work on personal development,

01:18:12.199 --> 01:18:12.813
you're going to get better,

01:18:13.764 --> 01:18:14.939
and you'll end up saving time,

01:18:15.403 --> 01:18:16.140
finding strategies,

01:18:16.462 --> 01:18:17.759
finding partners who will help you move faster!

01:18:17.881 --> 01:18:18.479
Because saving time,

01:18:18.942 --> 01:18:19.958
it's not just about your personal time,

01:18:20.502 --> 01:18:22.159
it's about saving time on what needs to get done,

01:18:22.422 --> 01:18:23.635
to get from point A to point B!

01:18:24.201 --> 01:18:25.300
So if tomorrow, what needs to happen,

01:18:25.460 --> 01:18:26.739
is that you, you want to do everything yourself,

01:18:26.920 --> 01:18:28.478
well obviously, you're going to hit a limit in your day!

01:18:28.822 --> 01:18:29.960
But if there are four things to do,

01:18:30.542 --> 01:18:32.939
like finding a property, raising funds,

01:18:33.301 --> 01:18:34.759
handling the execution, and selling,

01:18:35.081 --> 01:18:37.100
and you've got three other people on your team,

01:18:37.100 --> 01:18:38.338
it's all going to go way faster!

01:18:38.480 --> 01:18:40.597
And you're going to enjoy your life so much more!

01:18:40.840 --> 01:18:43.896
There's nothing worse than putting a fish on land!

01:18:44.882 --> 01:18:45.913
It just dies!

01:18:45.934 --> 01:18:46.539
A fish belongs in water!

01:18:46.579 --> 01:18:47.212
Right?

01:18:48.125 --> 01:18:48.939
Are we on the same page or not?

01:18:49.364 --> 01:18:50.680
If you're a freaking fish,

01:18:50.940 --> 01:18:52.454
you need to be in a freaking aquarium!

01:18:53.145 --> 01:18:53.576
In water!

01:18:53.822 --> 01:18:54.998
Sorry, I'm being a bit crude,

01:18:55.140 --> 01:18:56.359
I shouldn't, sorry, I'll take it back!

01:18:56.399 --> 01:18:56.565
Anyway!

01:18:57.201 --> 01:19:01.157
If you're a fish, you need to find your ocean!

01:19:08.300 --> 01:19:08.444
That's it!

01:19:09.722 --> 01:19:11.355
And if you're a monkey, you need to stay in the jungle!

01:19:12.405 --> 01:19:12.951
That's right!

01:19:12.990 --> 01:19:13.757
Don't go into the water!

01:19:13.980 --> 01:19:14.654
It's true!

01:19:15.020 --> 01:19:16.819
So try to figure out what kind of personality you have,

01:19:17.143 --> 01:19:17.894
so you can grow!

01:19:18.582 --> 01:19:20.680
This one stings, but it's so true!

01:19:20.739 --> 01:19:22.060
So today, I want to know,

01:19:22.341 --> 01:19:25.436
who really wants to have a portfolio worth 10 million or more?

01:19:26.502 --> 01:19:30.279
Honestly, I don't think there's any other way!

01:19:31.265 --> 01:19:31.774
You have to read!

01:19:32.240 --> 01:19:33.128
Eat well!

01:19:33.149 --> 01:19:33.815
Read books!

01:19:34.362 --> 01:19:35.136
Study on your own!

01:19:35.481 --> 01:19:36.475
Develop your mind!

01:19:36.940 --> 01:19:38.234
Become better and better!

01:19:39.041 --> 01:19:44.078
And above all, remember: you're your biggest investment!

01:19:44.804 --> 01:19:45.735
Invest in yourself!

01:19:46.462 --> 01:19:49.979
Most multimillionaires and people who really make a lot of money,

01:19:50.239 --> 01:19:51.279
we're talking way more than 10 million,

01:19:52.341 --> 01:19:53.627
they read between 40 and 60 books a year!

01:19:56.462 --> 01:19:58.117
And that's at least 30 minutes a day!

01:19:58.600 --> 01:20:00.079
Honestly, I'm telling you, it's a game changer,

01:20:00.260 --> 01:20:01.595
because it brings you so much!

01:20:02.161 --> 01:20:02.766
Manage your time!

01:20:05.201 --> 01:20:05.895
Uh... Ok!

01:20:10.622 --> 01:20:11.632
Ha ha!

01:20:11.653 --> 01:20:12.257
Give me a shot!

01:20:12.542 --> 01:20:13.380
I did it last year!

01:20:13.440 --> 01:20:14.317
Who was there, who remembers?

01:20:14.622 --> 01:20:15.295
Who was in my bed?

01:20:15.315 --> 01:20:15.396
Ok!

01:20:15.539 --> 01:20:16.537
Did I manage the timing or not?

01:20:16.761 --> 01:20:17.033
Yeah!

01:20:17.422 --> 01:20:18.073
Alright, great!

01:20:19.622 --> 01:20:20.760
I told you, 2 hours!

01:20:20.760 --> 01:20:20.886
Anyway!

01:20:21.220 --> 01:20:21.917
So, let's keep going!

01:20:22.061 --> 01:20:22.613
Managing your time!

01:20:23.100 --> 01:20:26.340
The day I realized a super simple quote from Richard Branson,

01:20:26.520 --> 01:20:26.945
it changed my life!

01:20:27.859 --> 01:20:28.436
Do you know what he said?

01:20:30.801 --> 01:20:32.777
We all have 24 hours in a day!

01:20:35.462 --> 01:20:36.373
Thanks Jean-Guillaume, seriously!

01:20:38.801 --> 01:20:41.399
Honestly, just for that, it was worth coming!

01:20:42.323 --> 01:20:43.132
Yeah, honestly!

01:20:43.659 --> 01:20:45.539
Well, when you think about it, it's true!

01:20:47.604 --> 01:20:47.815
Laughter

01:20:51.420 --> 01:20:52.270
It's true!

01:20:53.563 --> 01:20:54.414
So, what happens next?

01:20:55.702 --> 01:20:57.798
If you're not successful, it's because you're disorganized.

01:20:58.523 --> 01:20:59.698
You're not good at managing your time.

01:21:01.121 --> 01:21:05.020
How is it that some people are billionaires, hundred-millionaires,

01:21:05.300 --> 01:21:08.220
tens of millionaires, millionaires, have hundreds of thousands, tens of thousands,

01:21:08.539 --> 01:21:12.957
zero, minus 20,000 euros, minus 100,000, minus whatever!

01:21:13.724 --> 01:21:14.738
We all have 24 hours in a day!

01:21:16.180 --> 01:21:18.840
So, time management is super important!

01:21:19.720 --> 01:21:21.699
And for everyone in Money Game, I talk about this a lot,

01:21:24.301 --> 01:21:27.460
there’s a ton to do on this, and it’s definitely something you need to work on.

01:21:27.460 --> 01:21:29.920
So if you're not good at time management, read books about it and keep moving forward

01:21:30.542 --> 01:21:31.260
to get better.

01:21:32.021 --> 01:21:32.873
Take risks, my friends!

01:21:33.440 --> 01:21:37.279
Step out of your comfort zone—everything you want is on the other side.

01:21:37.561 --> 01:21:38.179
Okay, we talked about that.

01:21:38.439 --> 01:21:38.949
Oh damn, here we go!

01:21:40.641 --> 01:21:43.300
Ah, this is the moment, Jean-Guillaume, you were credible up until now.

01:21:44.480 --> 01:21:45.498
But now, you're about to lose all your credibility.

01:21:46.743 --> 01:21:47.377
Should I show you the video?

01:21:48.961 --> 01:21:49.779
No, this time, we're going to do the opposite.

01:21:50.279 --> 01:21:50.858
Yeah, we're going to do the opposite.

01:21:51.521 --> 01:21:53.319
I think it's better to do the opposite here.

01:21:54.740 --> 01:21:56.637
So now, I'm going to show you a video where...

01:21:58.521 --> 01:22:02.600
I personally invested, even with my partners, in a project that was incredible.

01:22:05.568 --> 01:22:06.038
It was in Dubai.

01:22:06.399 --> 01:22:11.139
That's actually what got us to invest there in the first place.

01:22:12.063 --> 01:22:13.818
And I believed in it so much that...

01:22:14.885 --> 01:22:15.920
Well, you'll see what happened.

01:22:17.082 --> 01:22:18.880
That project never happened.

01:22:20.762 --> 01:22:22.800
People did what we call the starfish.

01:22:23.801 --> 01:22:28.140
They did a lot of fundraising here, more fundraising there, and more fundraising over here.

01:22:28.682 --> 01:22:29.920
So in the end, they never finished the project.

01:22:30.684 --> 01:22:31.539
It dragged on for years.

01:22:31.539 --> 01:22:34.340
I personally invested hundreds of thousands of dollars.

01:22:35.322 --> 01:22:38.039
We also raised a bit of money from people who joined us in the project.

01:22:39.079 --> 01:22:40.680
And it's a shame there's no date on this.

01:22:41.664 --> 01:22:42.659
I'll give it to you if I find it.

01:22:42.899 --> 01:22:43.813
But it was at least...

01:22:44.983 --> 01:22:46.800
At least, I don't know, 8 years ago, something like that.

01:22:46.920 --> 01:22:47.155
Anyway.

01:22:47.907 --> 01:22:48.560
I look a bit different.

01:22:49.404 --> 01:22:49.679
Nice.

01:22:49.863 --> 01:22:50.197
Hey boys.

01:22:51.502 --> 01:22:52.537
Jean-Guillaume, Dubai.

01:22:53.765 --> 01:22:54.800
I came here two years ago.

01:22:55.561 --> 01:22:58.399
And I stopped right in front of this damn building.

01:22:59.300 --> 01:23:00.140
Well, this road.

01:23:00.560 --> 01:23:02.739
And here, it was exactly like it is now.

01:23:02.859 --> 01:23:03.435
Which is, absolutely nothing.

01:23:03.761 --> 01:23:04.500
And I had no idea.

01:23:05.061 --> 01:23:07.619
But that was where we were supposed to build the Swarovski tower.

01:23:08.822 --> 01:23:09.738
So right now as I'm talking to you,

01:23:10.625 --> 01:23:11.380
there's absolutely nothing here.

01:23:11.827 --> 01:23:12.199
Nothing at all.

01:23:12.780 --> 01:23:16.159
And they're going to build a Swarovski tower here,

01:23:16.442 --> 01:23:18.960
which will be as tall, maybe even taller than this one.

01:23:19.461 --> 01:23:21.739
We're talking about 800 meters, like the Burj Khalifa.

01:23:22.300 --> 01:23:23.539
It's going to be incredible.

01:23:23.920 --> 01:23:27.918
And the way the layout—the land—is set up...

01:23:29.003 --> 01:23:30.238
I could talk about this a lot longer,

01:23:30.560 --> 01:23:31.800
but I see the time and we have to keep things moving.

01:23:31.961 --> 01:23:32.413
Sound good?

01:23:34.000 --> 01:23:34.470
The project didn't happen.

01:23:35.359 --> 01:23:36.916
Can you imagine how embarrassed I am right now?

01:23:39.561 --> 01:23:41.199
So what I'm saying is, we're going to make mistakes.

01:23:42.023 --> 01:23:43.199
You're going to make mistakes, just be aware of that.

01:23:44.261 --> 01:23:45.979
It didn't happen because it wasn't a project

01:23:46.203 --> 01:23:47.079
that we controlled ourselves.

01:23:47.579 --> 01:23:49.100
So sometimes, you really have to be careful,

01:23:49.320 --> 01:23:50.599
especially when you start having a lot of cash

01:23:51.484 --> 01:23:52.600
and you want to start investing.

01:23:53.081 --> 01:23:54.699
Still, keep a big chunk in projects

01:23:54.863 --> 01:23:55.458
that you're in control of.

01:23:56.042 --> 01:23:58.039
And try to check out and dig into the people

01:23:58.039 --> 01:23:58.452
who are going to be managing things, etc.

01:23:59.104 --> 01:24:00.539
There are going to be issues.

01:24:01.122 --> 01:24:02.579
There will be some, you just need to know how to handle them.

01:24:03.141 --> 01:24:04.819
But don't make the same mistakes we did.

01:24:05.520 --> 01:24:07.359
So, all this to say, you have to keep going.

01:24:07.960 --> 01:24:10.140
Because after that, I took a real hit,

01:24:11.305 --> 01:24:12.279
minus 300,000 dollars,

01:24:13.841 --> 01:24:14.068
okay?

01:24:14.582 --> 01:24:16.180
That’s not just a hit, that’s a serious smackdown.

01:24:17.445 --> 01:24:18.100
A real smackdown.

01:24:20.028 --> 01:24:20.500
And if I’d stopped there,

01:24:21.582 --> 01:24:23.738
I wouldn’t have made 1.1 million dollars selling my main residence.

01:24:24.104 --> 01:24:24.896
We wouldn’t have made millions, and so on.

01:24:25.260 --> 01:24:25.855
Compared to that, and so on.

01:24:26.222 --> 01:24:26.859
You could easily say,

01:24:27.122 --> 01:24:28.039
but that’s just other people’s faith, I’m going for it.

01:24:28.220 --> 01:24:28.337
No.

01:24:29.823 --> 01:24:31.720
You just need to put yourself in a position

01:24:31.963 --> 01:24:32.819
to make as few mistakes as possible.

01:24:33.082 --> 01:24:33.738
Okay, I get it, I’m speeding up.

01:24:34.380 --> 01:24:34.699
Keep going.

01:24:35.220 --> 01:24:36.519
It's not about how hard you hit,

01:24:36.720 --> 01:24:38.719
it's about how hard you can get hit

01:24:38.800 --> 01:24:39.720
and keep moving forward.

01:24:40.225 --> 01:24:40.819
Perseverance,

01:24:40.899 --> 01:24:43.420
it’s not about whether you’ll take a hit.

01:24:43.703 --> 01:24:44.279
You will take some hits.

01:24:44.802 --> 01:24:46.260
The real question is, how long will it take you

01:24:46.904 --> 01:24:47.720
to get back up on your feet

01:24:47.902 --> 01:24:49.260
and move forward, to go even further.

01:24:52.181 --> 01:24:53.319
Always find a way to win.

01:24:54.141 --> 01:24:55.779
The 30 million in 30 days, that happened because

01:24:56.483 --> 01:24:57.859
no excuses allowed.

01:24:57.979 --> 01:24:59.238
And sometimes you'll lose, sometimes you'll win.

01:24:59.462 --> 01:25:00.180
We won that time.

01:25:00.502 --> 01:25:01.439
I've lost plenty of other times.

01:25:01.560 --> 01:25:02.340
There are lots of ideas that never happened.

01:25:03.362 --> 01:25:04.597
But if you believe in the industry, and so on,

01:25:04.739 --> 01:25:05.680
that's why you need 5 years.

01:25:06.161 --> 01:25:07.520
Because if you have your goal,

01:25:07.681 --> 01:25:08.680
and you haven't reached it yet, it's okay.

01:25:08.859 --> 01:25:09.859
It doesn't mean you won't get there.

01:25:10.180 --> 01:25:11.298
It just means it wasn't the right time

01:25:11.359 --> 01:25:12.069
and you need to be more patient.

01:25:13.523 --> 01:25:14.578
You need to find a time

01:25:14.905 --> 01:25:15.519
to do what you love.

01:25:16.819 --> 01:25:17.998
Always do what you love

01:25:18.444 --> 01:25:19.838
because otherwise, it's just going to be stressful.

01:25:20.539 --> 01:25:21.614
But if you do what you love,

01:25:22.039 --> 01:25:23.220
that's called passion.

01:25:23.340 --> 01:25:24.159
Me, I'm passionate about what I do.

01:25:24.680 --> 01:25:26.000
I honestly feel like I'm not working at all.

01:25:26.119 --> 01:25:26.595
I love what I do.

01:25:26.800 --> 01:25:27.278
I'm here with you.

01:25:27.619 --> 01:25:27.791
I love it.

01:25:28.300 --> 01:25:29.779
I'll be here until tonight.

01:25:30.180 --> 01:25:31.079
Because tomorrow, I'm heading out.

01:25:31.384 --> 01:25:32.020
So if you want to see me,

01:25:32.119 --> 01:25:32.579
we still have time to meet.

01:25:32.780 --> 01:25:34.300
We can chat, talk, I can give you advice.

01:25:34.943 --> 01:25:36.140
And that's really important too.

01:25:36.239 --> 01:25:36.717
So, once again,

01:25:36.840 --> 01:25:37.698
think about fish in water.

01:25:39.101 --> 01:25:40.137
Why don't people take action?

01:25:40.239 --> 01:25:40.658
Oh yeah, got it.

01:25:40.841 --> 01:25:41.399
Okay, that's where we're at.

01:25:41.460 --> 01:25:41.911
Alright, so,

01:25:43.640 --> 01:25:45.159
let's list them real quick.

01:25:45.260 --> 01:25:45.591
Take a picture.

01:25:46.484 --> 01:25:47.220
Fear of what others think.

01:25:47.542 --> 01:25:49.779
70% of people don't dare act because they're afraid of being judged.

01:25:50.283 --> 01:25:51.680
We don't give a damn what people think.

01:25:51.801 --> 01:25:52.498
We couldn't care less.

01:25:53.003 --> 01:25:53.439
Fear of failure.

01:25:53.902 --> 01:25:56.479
80% of people never start a project because they're afraid to fail.

01:25:56.966 --> 01:25:57.619
You're going to fail.

01:25:57.902 --> 01:25:58.880
That's part of success.

01:25:59.204 --> 01:25:59.699
You need to know that.

01:26:00.081 --> 01:26:01.095
So, what do we do now?

01:26:01.421 --> 01:26:01.998
Well, we keep going.

01:26:02.324 --> 01:26:02.408
Alright?

01:26:03.023 --> 01:26:04.479
We just try to limit the damage.

01:26:05.505 --> 01:26:06.078
Lack of clarity.

01:26:06.280 --> 01:26:07.680
You don't know what to do or where to start.

01:26:08.103 --> 01:26:09.579
50% give up because they don't have a clear plan.

01:26:09.579 --> 01:26:10.859
So, you need to clarify your plan.

01:26:10.960 --> 01:26:11.779
It's simple, but you have to do it.

01:26:12.420 --> 01:26:13.179
Analysis paralysis.

01:26:13.440 --> 01:26:15.619
Too much info, too much thinking, but zero action.

01:26:16.041 --> 01:26:19.579
70% of top performers spend their time taking action, not overthinking.

01:26:19.780 --> 01:26:21.539
At some point, yes, you have to do the work.

01:26:21.739 --> 01:26:23.259
But at some point, you have to take action.

01:26:23.500 --> 01:26:24.279
No, but I'm not ready.

01:26:24.380 --> 01:26:25.380
No, at some point, you just have to go for it.

01:26:26.064 --> 01:26:27.520
People know what to do.

01:26:27.702 --> 01:26:28.439
They just don't do it.

01:26:29.140 --> 01:26:29.336
So,

01:26:31.042 --> 01:26:34.778
I'm 97% sure you don't like me because I'm 100% sure I don't care.

01:26:37.323 --> 01:26:38.739
So, forget about what others think.

01:26:38.966 --> 01:26:39.439
7 tips.

01:26:39.881 --> 01:26:40.538
Never give up.

01:26:41.140 --> 01:26:42.319
Tony Robbins, one of my mentors.

01:26:42.479 --> 01:26:43.064
1977, age 17, 0 dollars.

01:26:45.060 --> 01:26:47.033
Today—or well, in 2021—age 61, 600 million dollars.

01:26:48.542 --> 01:26:49.779
He's one of the best guys in the business.

01:26:50.443 --> 01:26:51.319
Patience pays off.

01:26:51.962 --> 01:26:52.639
Seriously, patience pays.

01:26:52.921 --> 01:26:53.979
Warren Buffett, his net worth.

01:26:54.380 --> 01:26:56.100
Everyone always talks about Warren Buffett.

01:26:56.945 --> 01:26:57.259
Check this out.

01:26:59.300 --> 01:26:59.682
14, 5,000, 15, 6,000.

01:27:02.724 --> 01:27:03.600
Damn, he's not moving fast.

01:27:04.761 --> 01:27:06.675
19, 10,000, 21, 20,000.

01:27:08.021 --> 01:27:08.920
We're talking about Warren Buffett here.

01:27:10.740 --> 01:27:11.832
26, 140,000, 30, 1 million.

01:27:13.962 --> 01:27:16.539
It took him 16 years to make his first million.

01:27:17.966 --> 01:27:18.759
At 33, 2.4 million.

01:27:19.500 --> 01:27:20.300
Ah, now it's starting to look better.

01:27:20.380 --> 01:27:20.706
35, 37, 43 years old.

01:27:21.560 --> 01:27:22.376
And look, Warren Buffett, fucking legend.

01:27:24.243 --> 01:27:26.018
99% of his fortune was made after age 50.

01:27:27.201 --> 01:27:27.324
Okay?

01:27:27.862 --> 01:27:28.960
So for the folks who are a bit older out there—

01:27:29.500 --> 01:27:29.819
It's ok.

01:27:30.140 --> 01:27:30.738
It's gonna work out.

01:27:33.543 --> 01:27:35.039
Don't change a winning formula.

01:27:36.027 --> 01:27:36.699
Ah, I love this slide.

01:27:37.581 --> 01:27:38.154
Ah, this slide.

01:27:39.386 --> 01:27:40.038
This one's for focus.

01:27:41.229 --> 01:27:42.020
Set it as your wallpaper.

01:27:44.141 --> 01:27:45.913
Who hasn't dreamed of owning a luxury car?

01:27:47.061 --> 01:27:49.100
Well, now that I'm loaded,

01:27:49.944 --> 01:27:51.140
I bought myself a Lamborghini.

01:27:52.005 --> 01:27:52.716
Is that going to happen to you?

01:27:53.027 --> 01:27:53.159
Yeah.

01:27:57.948 --> 01:27:59.960
Not at all.

01:28:01.380 --> 01:28:03.119
I still have my damn Range Rover

01:28:03.119 --> 01:28:05.274
that I bought for 30,000 euros back in 2015.

01:28:07.899 --> 01:28:08.592
What's up?

01:28:09.884 --> 01:28:11.079
Oh, the Apollo? I sold that ages ago.

01:28:12.520 --> 01:28:14.939
That was in Dubai. The Range Rover, I couldn't bring it to Dubai.

01:28:15.319 --> 01:28:15.490
I admit.

01:28:16.399 --> 01:28:16.738
Stay in Geneva.

01:28:16.840 --> 01:28:16.976
Anyway.

01:28:18.002 --> 01:28:19.960
The clear message here is: Delay gratification.

01:28:20.060 --> 01:28:21.560
Could I afford to buy a Ferrari today?

01:28:21.628 --> 01:28:21.720
Yes.

01:28:22.060 --> 01:28:23.259
Could I afford to buy a Lamborghini?

01:28:23.386 --> 01:28:23.479
Yes.

01:28:23.859 --> 01:28:26.340
Could I afford a bunch of watches, a bunch of stuff, all sorts of things?

01:28:26.380 --> 01:28:26.475
Yes.

01:28:26.761 --> 01:28:27.380
But do I do it?

01:28:27.380 --> 01:28:27.467
No.

01:28:28.420 --> 01:28:31.319
Yeah, I have a few watches, that's true, to celebrate some success, two or three things.

01:28:32.300 --> 01:28:36.619
Ladies, a little Hermès bag here and there, that's fine, just a quick treat, if you really can't resist.

01:28:36.720 --> 01:28:37.970
Okay.

01:28:38.622 --> 01:28:41.939
But a car, that's just expenses, it's liabilities.

01:28:42.439 --> 01:28:42.847
It costs a lot.

01:28:44.340 --> 01:28:47.579
So, just because you can afford it and have money doesn't mean you should do it.

01:28:48.041 --> 01:28:52.340
I still want to stay hungry, I still want to wait, and I have a milestone—when I hit it,

01:28:52.902 --> 01:28:57.060
I'll buy myself the car I love, the one I rented for a weekend just to see what it felt like.

01:28:57.359 --> 01:29:01.720
Yeah, that's my car, and at some point I'll need a Lamborghini, because it's a bull, so Green Bull, you get it.

01:29:02.244 --> 01:29:02.594
So, there you go.

01:29:04.161 --> 01:29:04.739
Invest in yourself.

01:29:05.239 --> 01:29:05.957
Oh damn, I'm actually going to stay on schedule.

01:29:07.100 --> 01:29:09.693
Tony Robbins, that was February 28, 2014, in Faller-Derdale.

01:29:11.520 --> 01:29:14.079
I did 'Walk on Fire,' and it was one of the biggest changes in my life.

01:29:14.541 --> 01:29:16.859
I'm telling you, I've done a lot of conferences, a lot of events, and that changed my life.

01:29:17.319 --> 01:29:22.020
This photo is from March 28, 2026, just two days ago, I'm with my mentor, Patrick Bette-David,

01:29:22.220 --> 01:29:28.100
who built a network from 50 agents to 60,000 agents in the insurance industry.

01:29:28.480 --> 01:29:32.960
He sold it for 250 million, then started another business that's crushing it in consulting,

01:29:33.180 --> 01:29:35.659
he's my mentor, I was with him, I spend time with him.

01:29:36.301 --> 01:29:39.399
Do you know how much it cost me to be here, in terms of time, investment, and everything?

01:29:39.640 --> 01:29:46.619
I think over the last 12 months, I must have spent over 100,000 on trainings, going to places,

01:29:47.041 --> 01:29:49.078
doing my mastermind, speaking, and here we are.

01:29:49.180 --> 01:29:55.500
Well, you should put about 5 to 10% of what you earn into personal development, into yourself.

01:29:55.805 --> 01:29:56.840
That's what I think, anyway.

01:29:57.860 --> 01:30:02.279
So, I try to keep doing it because that's what helps me move forward.

01:30:02.399 --> 01:30:04.657
At some point, you just have to jump, guys, okay?

01:30:05.240 --> 01:30:06.572
Who's ever been skydiving here?

01:30:07.076 --> 01:30:07.359
Okay.

01:30:08.060 --> 01:30:11.259
And that feeling, who's actually gone up in a parachute?

01:30:11.702 --> 01:30:13.738
And honestly, you’re scared shitless, seriously.

01:30:14.220 --> 01:30:14.286
Okay.

01:30:14.981 --> 01:30:16.880
Come on, everyone, there’s a bit of exaggeration going on here.

01:30:17.359 --> 01:30:18.095
No, I’m kidding, I’m kidding.

01:30:18.962 --> 01:30:20.579
Alright, I’m good, I’m there.

01:30:21.280 --> 01:30:23.175
But how do you feel after you land?

01:30:23.819 --> 01:30:25.155
Isn’t that feeling just amazing?

01:30:25.921 --> 01:30:29.800
